      "type": "user-query",
      "text": "# Community Launchpad — Autoregression Test Report\n**Date:** 2026-06-20 | **Branch:** main | **Stack:** Vue 3 + Vite 8 + Frappe target\n\n---\n\n## 1. The Full Frappe Stack\n\nThis project is a **high-fidelity UX prototype** running on an in-memory mock today, with every TypeScript type 1:1 mirroring real Frappe DocType field names. The production target stack is:\n\n| Layer | App / Package | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Platform** | `frappe/frappe` | Auth, ORM, REST API, job queues, audit log, email |\n| **Community** | `frappe/gameplan` | Teams → Spaces (GP Project) → Posts (GP Discussion) → Comments → Reactions |\n| **Learning** | `frappe/lms` | Courses, Chapters, Lessons, Quizzes, Certificates, Enrollment |\n| **Messaging** | `frappe/raven` (The Commit Company) | Direct messages (Raven Channel + Raven Message) |\n| **Support** | `frappe/helpdesk` | Member support tickets + safeguarding triage queue |\n| **Handbook** | `frappe/wiki` | Community handbook, code of conduct |\n| **Analytics** | `frappe/insights` | Admin dashboards |\n| **Gamification** | `frappe/eps` | Energy Points System + badge awards |\n| **Custom** | `fg_companion` *(this repo, ~1 500 lines Python)* | FG Events, Mentor Matching, AI sentiment, vector search, moderation hooks |\n| **Frontend** | Vue 3 + TypeScript + Vite 8 | Client SPA (proxies to Frappe at `:8000/api`) |\n| **Styling** | Tailwind CSS v4 + `frappe-ui` | Design tokens, components |\n\n> **Note:** The README still says \"React 19 + TanStack Router\" in several places — the codebase was migrated to **Vue 3 + Vue Router 4** and Vite. The README docs/architecture diagrams are the only artefacts that haven't been updated.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Build & Lint Status\n\n### `npm run build` ✅ PASS\n\n```\n✓ built in 1.15s\n```\n\nAll 23 chunks emitted cleanly. The `[lightningcss minify] Unknown at rule: @utility / @custom-variant / @theme` warnings are **expected** — these are Tailwind v4 custom at-rules that lightningcss minifier doesn't understand at the CSS level but Vite's Tailwind plugin handles correctly before minification. They do **not** affect runtime behaviour.\n\n### `npm run lint` ⚠️ BROKEN (blocked, non-runtime)\n\nESLint config (`eslint.config.js`) imports `eslint-plugin-react-hooks` and `eslint-plugin-react-refresh`, which are **React plugins not installed** (the project was migrated to Vue). This breaks lint entirely.\n\n```\nError [ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND]: Cannot find package 'eslint-plugin-react-hooks'\n```\n\n**Impact:** Lint CI gate is non-functional. No runtime impact.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Frontend Route Regression\n\n### Architecture confirmed\n\n- **Router:** `src/main.ts` → Vue Router 4 with `createWebHistory`\n- **Store bridge:** `src/data/store.ts` wraps `src/mock-data/store.ts` — all 19 components import from `@/data/store` correctly (confirmed with grep)\n- **Dev server:** Vite on port 8080, proxying `/api` to `localhost:8000`\n\n### Route Matrix\n\n| Route | File | Store imports | Template correctness | Verdict |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `/` Home Feed | `HomeView.vue` | `getDiscussions` ✅ | PostCard loop, RouterLink ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/events` Events | `EventsView.vue` | `getEvents, getAttendees, getMyRSVP, setRSVP, getProject, getUser` ✅ | RSVP button loops, date formatting ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/members` Members | `MembersView.vue` | `getUsers` ✅ | Member card loop ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/members/:userId` Profile | `MemberDetailView.vue` | `getUser, getRecentPostsByUser, openOrCreateDMWith, currentUserId` ✅ | Profile card, posts list ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/courses` Courses | `CoursesView.vue` | `getCourses, getEnrollment, courseProgressPercent` ✅ | Course cards, progress ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/courses/new` New Course | `CourseNewView.vue` | `createCourse` ✅ | Form inputs, submit ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/courses/:courseId` Detail | `CourseDetailView.vue` | `getCourse, getChaptersForCourse, getLessonsForChapter, enrollInCourse, addChapter, addLesson, isLessonComplete` ✅ | Chapter/lesson tree, enroll button ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/courses/:courseId/lessons/:lessonId` | `LessonView.vue` | `getCourse, getLesson, isLessonComplete, markLessonComplete, enrollInCourse` ✅ | YouTube iframe, prev/next nav ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/mentors` Mentors | `MentorsView.vue` | `currentUserId, getMatchesForUser, getUser, getUsers, requestMentor` ✅ | Match cards, request modal ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/messages` Messages | `MessagesView.vue` | `getDMThreadsForUser, getOtherMember, getUser, currentUserId` ✅ | Thread list sidebar, RouterView slot ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/messages/:threadId` Thread | `ThreadView.vue` | `currentUserId, getDMMessages, getDMThread, getOtherMember, getUser, markThreadRead, sendDM` ✅ | Message bubbles, send form ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/notifications` | `NotificationsView.vue` | `getNotifications, markAllNotificationsRead, markNotificationRead` ✅ | Notification list ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/posts/:postId` Post Detail | `PostDetailView.vue` | Full store import ✅ | Article, comments, reactions, similar posts ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/spaces/:spaceId` Space | `SpaceView.vue` | `getDiscussions, getProject` ✅ | PostCard loop, NewPostModal ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/settings` Settings | `SettingsView.vue` | `getSSOProviders, getUser, getUserSettings, updateProfile, updateSSOProvider, updateUserSettings, currentUserId` ✅ | 5 tabs, Toggle components, SSO table ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n| `/docs` Docs | `DocsView.vue` | No store (static list) ✅ | Docs card list ✅ | ✅ PASS |\n\n**All 16 routes: ✅ PASS (static analysis)**\n\n---\n\n## 4. Component Regression\n\n| Component | File | Verdict | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `AppLayout` | `AppLayout.vue` | ✅ PASS | Sidebar teams/spaces loop, unread DM/notif badges, profile menu, New Post button |\n| `AppAvatar` | `AppAvatar.vue` | ✅ PASS | `getUser` import, initials fallback |\n| `PostCard` | `PostCard.vue` | ✅ PASS | `getProject, getUser, mockSentiment, getAISettings, getReactionsFor` |\n| `NewPostModal` | `NewPostModal.vue` | ✅ PASS | `createDiscussion, getProjects`, form + submit |\n| `SentimentBadge` | `SentimentBadge.vue` | ✅ PASS | Label → colour mapping |\n| `SidebarItem` | `SidebarItem.vue` | ✅ PASS | Simple RouterLink wrapper |\n| `Toggle` | `Toggle.vue` | ✅ PASS | Used in Settings; `@change` emitter |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Interaction / Mutation Regression\n\nAll mutations operate on the in-memory store via `src/data/store.ts` → `src/mock-data/store.ts`. Verified by code audit:\n\n| Interaction | Store function | Logic verified | Verdict |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Create post | `createDiscussion()` | Pushes to `state.discussions`, bumps `project.discussions_count`, emits | ✅ PASS |\n| Post comment | `createComment()` | Pushes to `state.comments`, updates `discussion.comments_count` + `last_post_at` | ✅ PASS |\n| Toggle emoji reaction | `toggleReaction()` | Splice/push in `state.reactions`, re-emits | ✅ PASS |\n| RSVP to event | `setRSVP()` | Upserts `state.attendees`, emits | ✅ PASS |\n| Request mentor | `requestMentor()` | Pushes `FGMentorMatch{status:\"Requested\"}` | ✅ PASS |\n| Enroll in course | `enrollInCourse()` | Guard against double-enroll, pushes enrollment, bumps `course.enrollments` | ✅ PASS |\n| Mark lesson complete | `markLessonComplete()` | Upserts progress, updates enrollment percent | ✅ PASS |\n| Send DM | `sendDM()` | Pushes message, updates thread preview + timestamp | ✅ PASS |\n| Mark thread read | `markThreadRead()` | Adds `currentUserId` to `read_by` on each message | ✅ PASS |\n| Update user settings | `updateUserSettings()` | Object.assign + emit | ✅ PASS |\n| Update profile | `updateProfile()` | Object.assign + emit | ✅ PASS |\n| Toggle SSO provider | `updateSSOProvider()` | Object.assign + mock `client_id_set` logic | ✅ PASS |\n| Create course | `createCourse()` | Creates course + auto-creates Chapter 1 | ✅ PASS |\n| Add chapter | `addChapter()` | Pushes chapter, sets `idx` | ✅ PASS |\n| Add lesson | `addLesson()` | Pushes lesson, updates `course.lessons` count | ✅ PASS |\n| Mark notifications read | `markAllNotificationsRead()` | Sets all `.read = true` | ✅ PASS |\n| Open/create DM thread | `openOrCreateDMWith()` | Find-or-create thread | ✅ PASS |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Python Backend (`fg_companion`) — Static Audit\n\n> Note: `fg_companion` requires a live Frappe bench (not running locally). Audited by code review.\n\n### `fg_companion/api.py`\n\n| Endpoint | Description | Verdict |\n|---|---|---|\n| `rsvp(event, rsvp_status)` | Upserts `FG Event Attendee`, calls `frappe.db.commit()` | ✅ Correct |\n| `similar_discussions(name)` | Delegates to `fg_companion.ai.vectors.query_similar` | ✅ Correct |\n| `toggle_reaction(reference_doctype, reference_name, emoji)` | Find-or-delete `GP Reaction`, uses `@frappe.whitelist()` | ✅ Correct |\n\n### `fg_companion/ai/sentiment.py`\n\n| Function | Verdict | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `enqueue_score(doc, method)` | ✅ Correct | Reads `FG AI Settings`, enqueues background job |\n| `analyze_sentiment(doctype, name)` | ✅ Correct | Strips HTML, calls `run_inference`, saves via `doc.db_set` to avoid loops |\n| `run_inference(text)` | ✅ Correct (with caveat) | ONNX import block has a bare `pass` after `import onnxruntime` — the model loading code was never filled in. Falls through to keyword fallback always. |\n\n> ⚠️ **Known gap:** ONNX model loading is a stub (`pass`). Keyword fallback always runs. Real ONNX inference needs the model file + tokenizer wired up.\n\n### `fg_companion/ai/vectors.py`\n\n| Function | Verdict | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `enqueue_vector_update(doc, method)` | ✅ Correct | Checks settings, enqueues |\n| `update_vector(name)` | ✅ Correct (with caveat) | Uses pgvector `ON CONFLICT ... DO UPDATE` syntax — this is PostgreSQL syntax, not MariaDB. Frappe defaults to MariaDB. Needs pgvector extension or DB switch. |\n| `delete_vector(doc, method)` | ✅ Correct | Silently swallows errors |\n| `query_similar(name, limit)` | ✅ Correct | ANN query + fallback to SQL LIKE on error |\n| `compute_embedding(text)` | ⚠️ STUB | Returns `random.uniform(-1,1)` seeded by hash. Not real embeddings. |\n\n> ⚠️ **Known gap:** Vector embeddings are random mock values. Real sentence-transformers/ONNX embedding model needed.\n\n### `hooks.py`\n\n| Hook | Verdict |\n|---|---|\n| `doc_events[\"GP Discussion\"][\"after_insert\"]` → sentiment | ✅ Correct |\n| `doc_events[\"GP Discussion\"][\"on_update\"]` → sentiment | ✅ Correct |\n| `doc_events[\"GP Discussion\"][\"on_trash\"]` → vector delete | ✅ Correct |\n| `doc_events[\"GP Comment\"][\"after_insert/on_update\"]` → sentiment | ✅ Correct |\n| `fixtures` for `fg_sentiment_label`, `fg_sentiment_score` Custom Fields | ✅ Correct |\n\n### DocTypes defined\n\n- `FG AI Settings` — Single DocType for sentinel config ✅\n- `FG Event` — Event record ✅\n- `FG Event Attendee` — RSVP child ✅\n- `FG Mentor Match` — Mentor pairing ✅\n\n---\n\n## 7. Store Version / Reactivity\n\nThe reactive store uses a pub/sub pattern (`listeners` Set + `emit()` + `useStoreVersion()` composable). All mutations call `emit()` correctly. Vue components using `computed()` with store selectors will re-render on mutation because `useStoreVersion()` drives the reactive version counter.\n\n**Verdict: ✅ PASS**\n\n---\n\n## 8. Issues Found\n\n| # | Severity | Category | Issue | Fix needed? |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | 🟡 Medium | Lint / DX | `eslint.config.js` imports `eslint-plugin-react-hooks` and `eslint-plugin-react-refresh` — React plugins not in `package.json` → `npm run lint` fails with `ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND` | Replace with Vue-appropriate ESLint plugins or remove |\n| 2 | 🟡 Medium | README drift | README says \"React 19 + TanStack Router\", references `.tsx` files and `src/routes/`. Actual code is Vue 3 + Vue Router 4 with `.vue` files in `src/views/` | Update README |\n| 3 | 🟡 Medium | Python / AI | ONNX sentiment model loading is a `pass` stub — keyword fallback always runs | Wire up real ONNX model when ready |\n| 4 | 🟡 Medium | Python / AI | `compute_embedding()` returns random vectors — not real embeddings | Wire sentence-transformers or ONNX embedding model |\n| 5 | 🟡 Medium | Python / DB | `vectors.py` uses PostgreSQL `ON CONFLICT` syntax — incompatible with MariaDB (Frappe default) | Confirm DB is PostgreSQL + pgvector, or use `INSERT OR REPLACE` |\n| 6 | 🟢 Low | UX | Settings > Appearance tab has a hardcoded `settings.timezone` display — no way to change it in UI | Add timezone selector (can be a `<select>` with common zones) |\n| 7 | 🟢 Low | DX | `eslint.config.js` also references `typescript-eslint` which is not in `package.json` | Add or remove |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Overall Verdict\n\n| Category | Result |\n|---|---|\n| TypeScript build | ✅ **PASS** — clean, 1.15s |\n| All 16 routes render | ✅ **PASS** — all templates, imports, and store selectors correct |\n| All 17 mutations | ✅ **PASS** — store functions correct, emit/reactivity intact |\n| All 7 components | ✅ **PASS** — correct imports and template bindings |\n| `fg_companion` Python API | ✅ **PASS** (with known stubs) |\n| ESLint | ❌ **FAIL** — React plugin not found (non-runtime) |\n| README accuracy | ❌ **Stale** — still describes React/TanStack codebase |\n\n### 🟢 Overall: **PASS** (prototype is fully functional)\n\nThe two failures (ESLint config, README) are non-runtime issues that do not affect user experience or prototype functionality. The app builds cleanly, all routes resolve, all mutations work correctly, and the Python backend is structurally sound (with the expected AI stubs).\n\n\ni need fix find it on my pc also create a folder for it that has all the code as is and htat it not just git and then ensure to mark each version as you working on it and make it work as its suppse cause if u read the adr and gherking and doc sits neeed to look like circle.so just like i had designed it and also its orginal lovable project before i refactored it to work fully.",
