      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto\\README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # FirstGens Community — Platform Prototype & Blueprint\n2: \n3: > **First-generation university students deserve a community platform that truly understands them.**\n4: > This repository is both the clickable prototype (run it today) *and* the complete technical blueprint for the production Frappe-powered platform it will become.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## Table of Contents\n9: \n10: 1. [What this is](#1-what-this-is)\n11: 2. [What this will become](#2-what-this-will-become)\n12: 3. [Running it right now](#3-running-it-right-now)\n13: 4. [Architecture overview](#4-architecture-overview)\n14: 5. [User journeys — Mermaid flowcharts](#5-user-journeys--mermaid-flowcharts)\n15:    - 5.1 [New member onboarding](#51-new-member-onboarding)\n16:    - 5.2 [Posting in a Space](#52-posting-in-a-space)\n17:    - 5.3 [Mentor match flow](#53-mentor-match-flow)\n18:    - 5.4 [Event RSVP flow](#54-event-rsvp-flow)\n19:    - 5.5 [Course enrolment & progress](#55-course-enrolment--progress)\n20:    - 5.6 [Direct messages (Raven)](#56-direct-messages-raven)\n21:    - 5.7 [Safeguarding & moderation pipeline](#57-safeguarding--moderation-pipeline)\n22:    - 5.8 [Paywall / membership gating](#58-paywall--membership-gating)\n23:    - 5.9 [Gamification & badge award](#59-gamification--badge-award)\n24:    - 5.10 [Weekly community digest](#510-weekly-community-digest)\n25:    - 5.11 [Full platform data flow](#511-full-platform-data-flow)\n26: 6. [Project structure](#6-project-structure)\n27: 7. [Pages & routes](#7-pages--routes)\n28: 8. [Mock data & schema contract](#8-mock-data--schema-contract)\n29: 9. [The Frappe DNA — why this stack](#9-the-frappe-dna--why-this-stack)\n30: 10. [The Circle.so DNA — feature parity map](#10-the-circleso-dna--feature-parity-map)\n31: 11. [Documentation index](#11-documentation-index)\n32: 12. [How long to production?](#12-how-long-to-production)\n33: 13. [Contributing & branch rules](#13-contributing--branch-rules)\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 1. What this is\n38: \n39: **A high-fidelity, clickable UX/UI prototype** for a community platform supporting first-generation university students in the UK. It exists so stakeholders, designers, and prospective users can:\n40: \n41: - Click through realistic end-to-end flows before a single production database row is written\n42: - Validate the information architecture\n43: - Sign off UX decisions as Gherkin scenarios (see [`docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md`](docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md))\n44: - Confirm that the data model is schema-faithful to the real Frappe backend\n45: \n46: **Tech stack (prototype only):**\n47: \n48: | Layer | Choice | Why |\n49: |---|---|---|\n50: | UI framework | React 19 + TypeScript | Type-safe components that mirror Frappe shapes |\n51: | Router | TanStack Router / TanStack Start | File-based routing, SSR-ready |\n52: | Server | Nitro (via `@lovable.dev/vite-tanstack-config`) | Thin SSR wrapper, Cloudflare-ready |\n53: | Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (Radix primitives) | Rapid design-system iteration |\n54: | State / data | In-memory mock store (`src/mock-data/`) | No backend needed for prototype |\n55: | Query | TanStack Query v5 | Mirrors how real Frappe data will be fetched |\n56: | Dev tooling | Bun, Vite 8, ESLint, Prettier | Fast iteration |\n57: \n58: **Important:** there is no database, no auth, no external API call in this prototype. A full page reload resets all in-memory state to the seeded mock data.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 2. What this will become\n63: \n64: The production system will be built on the **Frappe Framework**, composing:\n65: \n66: | App | Role |\n67: |---|---|\n68: | [`frappe/frappe`](https://github.com/frappe/frappe) | Platform: auth, ORM, REST, jobs, audit log |\n69: | [`frappe/gameplan`](https://github.com/frappe/gameplan) | Community: Teams, Spaces (Projects), Posts (Discussions), Comments, Reactions |\n70: | [`frappe/lms`](https://github.com/frappe/lms) | Learning: Courses, Chapters, Lessons, Quizzes, Certificates |\n71: | [`frappe/raven`](https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven) | Direct messaging + channels |\n72: | [`frappe/helpdesk`](https://github.com/frappe/helpdesk) | Member support + safeguarding triage |\n73: | [`frappe/wiki`](https://github.com/frappe/wiki) | Community handbook, code of conduct |\n74: | [`frappe/insights`](https://github.com/frappe/insights) | Analytics dashboards |\n75: | [`frappe/eps`](https://github.com/frappe/eps) | Gamification / Energy Points |\n76: | `fg_companion` *(new, ~1,500 lines Python)* | Events, mentor matching, AI hooks, moderation, polls, badges |\n77: \n78: The prototype's TypeScript types in [`src/mock-data/types.ts`](src/mock-data/types.ts) are **deliberately 1:1 with real Frappe DocType field names**. The porting work is a data-layer swap, not a redesign. See [`docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md`](docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md) and [`docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md`](docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md).\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 3. Running it right now\n83: \n84: ### Prerequisites\n85: \n86: | Tool | Minimum version | Check |\n87: |---|---|---|\n88: | [Node.js](https://nodejs.org) | 20 LTS | `node -v` |\n89: | [Bun](https://bun.sh) | 1.1+ | `bun -v` |\n90: | Git | any recent | `git --version` |\n91: \n92: > **Windows note:** Bun runs natively on Windows. All commands below work in PowerShell, CMD, or Git Bash.\n93: \n94: ### Clone & install\n95: \n96: ```bash\n97: git clone https://github.com/andiekobbietks/community-launchpad-proto.git\n98: cd community-launchpad-proto\n99: bun install\n100: ```\n101: \n102: ### Start the dev server\n103: \n104: ```bash\n105: bun run dev\n106: ```\n107: \n108: Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000). Hot-module replacement is enabled — file saves are reflected instantly.\n109: \n110: ### Available scripts\n111: \n112: | Script | What it does |\n113: |---|---|\n114: | `bun run dev` | Starts Vite dev server with HMR on port 3000 |\n115: | `bun run build` | Production build (Nitro SSR bundle + static assets) |\n116: | `bun run build:dev` | Dev-mode build (useful for debugging) |\n117: | `bun run preview` | Serves the production build locally |\n118: | `bun run lint` | ESLint across all TypeScript/React files |\n119: | `bun run format` | Prettier format all files |\n120: \n121: ### Resetting state\n122: \n123: The mock store is **in-memory only**. Any change you make (new post, RSVP, mentor request) lives only for the current browser tab session. A full page reload (`F5` / `⌘R`) restores the seed data exactly as committed.\n124: \n125: ### The walkthrough overlay\n126: \n127: When you first open the app you'll see a guided walkthrough overlay (`src/components/Walkthrough.tsx`). Click **Next** to step through all prototype screens, or click **Skip** to go straight to the home feed. The overlay stores its state in `sessionStorage` so it only shows once per browser tab.\n128: \n129: ### Navigating the prototype\n130: \n131: | Route | What you see |\n132: |---|---|\n133: | `/` | Home feed — posts from all joined Spaces, newest first |\n134: | `/spaces/:spaceId` | Single Space with post list + **New Post** composer |\n135: | `/posts/:postId` | Full post + threaded comments + \"Similar posts\" AI stub |\n136: | `/events` | Event card grid; click **RSVP** to mutate in-memory attendees |\n137: | `/mentors` | Request a mentor + view your current matches |\n138: | `/courses` | Course catalogue stub (real LMS: `frappe/lms`) |\n139: | `/members` | Member directory |\n140: | `/members/:userId` | Member profile — bio, posts, badges |\n141: | `/messages` | DM thread list (Raven prototype) |\n142: | `/messages/:threadId` | Single DM conversation |\n143: | `/notifications` | Notification inbox |\n144: | `/settings` | Full settings panel — notifications, privacy, integrations, AI |\n145: | `/docs` | In-app documentation panel |\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## 4. Architecture overview\n150: \n151: ```\n152: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n153: │                   Browser (React 19 + TanStack Router)               │\n154: │                                                                      │\n155: │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────┐ │\n156: │  │  AppLayout   │  │   Pages /   │  │  Components  │  │  Hooks   │ │\n157: │  │ (nav, side-  │  │   Routes    │  │ PostCard,    │  │ useStore │ │\n158: │  │  bar, shell) │  │ (19 files)  │  │ SentimentBdg │  │ etc.     │ │\n159: │  └──────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────┘ │\n160: │                              │                                       │\n161: │              ┌───────────────▼────────────────┐                     │\n162: │              │     src/mock-data/store.ts      │                     │\n163: │              │  (in-memory reactive store)     │                     │\n164: │              │  seed.ts → typed arrays         │                     │\n165: │              │  types.ts → DocType mirror      │                     │\n166: │              └───────────────────────────────  │                     │\n167: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n168: \n169: Production target (Frappe bench):\n170: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n171: │  frappe/frappe  (platform layer)                    │\n172: │  ├─ frappe/gameplan  (Teams / Spaces / Posts)       │\n173: │  ├─ frappe/lms       (Courses / Lessons / Certs)    │\n174: │  ├─ frappe/raven     (DMs / Channels)               │\n175: │  ├─ frappe/helpdesk  (Support / Safeguarding)       │\n176: │  ├─ frappe/wiki      (Handbook / Policies)          │\n177: │  ├─ frappe/insights  (Analytics)                    │\n178: │  ├─ frappe/eps       (Gamification)                 │\n179: │  └─ fg_companion     (Events, Mentors, AI, Polls)   │\n180: │       ├─ DocTypes: FG Event, FG Mentor Match, …     │\n181: │       ├─ doc_events → sentiment, vector search      │\n182: │       └─ @frappe.whitelist() RPC endpoints          │\n183: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n184: ```\n185: \n186: The React frontend talks to Frappe via:\n187: - `GET /api/resource/<DocType>` — list / get\n188: - `POST /api/method/frappe.client.insert` — create\n189: - `PUT /api/resource/<DocType>/<name>` — update\n190: - `POST /api/method/fg_companion.api.<function>` — custom RPC\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ## 5. User journeys — Mermaid flowcharts\n195: \n196: Each flowchart maps directly to a Gherkin scenario in [`docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md`](docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md) and a production ADR in [`docs/adr/`](docs/adr/).\n197: \n198: ### 5.1 New member onboarding\n199: \n200: ```mermaid\n201: flowchart TD\n202:     A([Visitor lands on /]) --> B{Signed in?}\n203:     B -- No --> C[Social Login / Email OTP\\nFrappe Social Login Key]\n204:     C --> D[Profile setup wizard\\nGP User Profile: bio, image, interests]\n205:     D --> E[Space discovery\\nList of GP Projects by visibility]\n206:     E --> F{Join Spaces}\n207:     F --> G[Home feed populates\\nGP Discussion filtered by joined Projects]\n208:     G --> H[Walkthrough overlay\\nfirst-time guide]\n209:     H --> I([Member is active])\n210:     B -- Yes --> G\n211: ```\n212: \n213: ### 5.2 Posting in a Space\n214: \n215: ```mermaid\n216: flowchart TD\n217:     A([Member opens a Space]) --> B[Space page loads\\n/spaces/:spaceId]\n218:     B --> C[Click 'New Post']\n219:     C --> D[NewPostModal opens\\ntitle + rich text body]\n220:     D --> E{Attach poll?}\n221:     E -- Yes --> F[Poll composer\\nfg_poll DocType]\n222:     E -- No --> G\n223:     F --> G[Submit post\\nPOST GP Discussion]\n224:     G --> H[doc_event: after_insert\\nfg_companion.ai.sentiment.enqueue_score]\n225:     H --> I{Sentiment score\\n>= threshold?}\n226:     I -- Yes --> J[fg_sentiment_label = Needs Attention\\nModeration queue entry]\n227:     I -- No --> K[Post appears in feed\\nranked by recency × reactions]\n228:     J --> K\n229:     K --> L[EPS points awarded\\n+10 for first post]\n230:     L --> M{First post ever?}\n231:     M -- Yes --> N[fg_badge_award: 'First Post' badge]\n232:     M -- No --> O([Done])\n233:     N --> O\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ### 5.3 Mentor match flow\n237: \n238: ```mermaid\n239: flowchart TD\n240:     A([Student visits /mentors]) --> B[Member directory filtered\\nrole = Mentor]\n241:     B --> C[Click 'Request Mentor Match']\n242:     C --> D[POST fg_companion.api.request_mentor\\nFG Mentor Match status = Requested]\n243:     D --> E[Mentor receives\\nNotification Log entry]\n244:     E --> F{Mentor accepts?}\n245:     F -- No --> G[Status = Declined\\nStudent notified]\n246:     F -- Yes --> H[Status = Active\\nfg_mentor_match.on_accept hook]\n247:     H --> I[Raven DM channel created\\nwith system message 'Match accepted on date']\n248:     I --> J[Both parties see\\nMessage Joel / Message Maya button]\n249:     J --> K{Session complete?}\n250:     K -- No --> L([Ongoing mentorship])\n251:     K -- Yes --> M[Status = Completed\\nEPS points for mentor]\n252:     M --> N([Match closed])\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ### 5.4 Event RSVP flow\n256: \n257: ```mermaid\n258: flowchart TD\n259:     A([Member visits /events]) --> B[Event grid loads\\nFG Event list view]\n260:     B --> C[Click event card]\n261:     C --> D{event_type?}\n262:     D -- Teams --> E[fg_live_event\\nprovider = teams\\nMicrosoft Graph join_url]\n263:     D -- Internal --> F[frappe/meet WebRTC room]\n264:     D -- BBB --> G[BigBlueButton room]\n265:     D -- In Person --> H[Physical address shown\\n.ics download]\n266:     E & F & G & H --> I[Click RSVP button]\n267:     I --> J[POST fg_companion.api.rsvp\\nFG Event Attendee upsert]\n268:     J --> K{capacity reached?}\n269:     K -- Yes --> L[Waitlist notification\\nEmail Queue entry]\n270:     K -- No --> M[rsvp_status = Going\\nConfirmation email + .ics]\n271:     M --> N([User sees Going badge on card])\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ### 5.5 Course enrolment & progress\n275: \n276: ```mermaid\n277: flowchart TD\n278:     A([Member visits /courses]) --> B[LMS Course catalogue\\nfrappe/lms]\n279:     B --> C{paid_course?}\n280:     C -- Yes --> D[Paywall lock screen\\nfg_space.paywall_plan]\n281:     D --> E{Subscribed?}\n282:     E -- No --> F[Stripe checkout\\nfrappe/payments]\n283:     F --> G[fg_paywall_grant created\\nStripe webhook]\n284:     E -- Yes --> H\n285:     G --> H[Enrol: LMS Enrollment insert]\n286:     C -- No --> H\n287:     H --> I[Course detail page\\nChapters + Lessons]\n288:     I --> J[Open lesson\\n/courses/:id/lessons/:lessonId]\n289:     J --> K{YouTube video?}\n290:     K -- Yes --> L[YouTube embed\\nshortcode player]\n291:     K -- No --> M[Markdown body renders]\n292:     L & M --> N[Mark lesson complete\\nLMS Course Progress = Complete]\n293:     N --> O{All lessons done?}\n294:     O -- No --> I\n295:     O -- Yes --> P[LMS Certificate generated\\nPDF print format]\n296:     P --> Q[EPS points awarded\\n+100 course completion]\n297:     Q --> R([Certificate in profile])\n298: ```\n299: \n300: ### 5.6 Direct messages (Raven)\n301: \n302: ```mermaid\n303: flowchart TD\n304:     A([User clicks 'Message X']) --> B{DM channel exists?}\n305:     B -- No --> C[Create Raven DM channel\\nRaven Channel insert]\n306:     C --> D[System message: 'Conversation started']\n307:     B -- Yes --> E\n308:     D --> E[/messages/:threadId loads]\n309:     E --> F[Message list renders\\nRaven Message list]\n310:     F --> G[User types message]\n311:     G --> H[POST Raven Message insert]\n312:     H --> I[Real-time update\\nFrappe WebSocket / Frappe Desk]\n313:     I --> J{Other party online?}\n314:     J -- No --> K[Push notification\\nFCM via Frappe Framework]\n315:     J -- Yes --> L[Message appears instantly]\n316:     K & L --> M([Conversation active])\n317:     M --> N{Matched via mentor match?}\n318:     N -- Yes --> O[First system message\\nMatch accepted on date]\n319:     N -- No --> P([Standard DM])\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### 5.7 Safeguarding & moderation pipeline\n323: \n324: ```mermaid\n325: flowchart TD\n326:     A([New post submitted]) --> B[GP Discussion insert]\n327:     B --> C[doc_event: after_insert\\nfg_companion.ai.sentiment.enqueue_score]\n328:     C --> D{enable_sentiment = 1?}\n329:     D -- No --> E([Post published normally])\n330:     D -- Yes --> F[Background worker\\nONNX sentiment model runs]\n331:     F --> G{neg score >= threshold?}\n332:     G -- No --> H[fg_sentiment_label = Neutral/Positive]\n333:     H --> E\n334:     G -- Yes --> I[fg_sentiment_label = Needs Attention\\nfg_sentiment_score written]\n335:     I --> J[Moderation queue entry\\nfg_moderation_queue row]\n336:     J --> K[Helpdesk ticket auto-opened\\nAssigned to Trusted Reviewer]\n337:     K --> L[Space Admin sees amber badge\\non post card — not visible to members]\n338:     L --> M{Reviewer decision}\n339:     M -- Approve --> N[Status cleared\\nPost remains]\n340:     M -- Reject --> O[Post hidden\\nAuthor notified]\n341:     M -- Edit --> P[Admin edits + approves]\n342:     O --> Q{Author appeals?}\n343:     Q -- Yes --> R[Helpdesk appeal ticket]\n344:     Q -- No --> S([Case closed])\n345:     R --> T([Second review])\n346: ```\n347: \n348: ### 5.8 Paywall / membership gating\n349: \n350: ```mermaid\n351: flowchart TD\n352:     A([User clicks a Space with paywall]) --> B{fg_paywall_grant exists?}\n353:     B -- Yes --> C[Enter Space normally]\n354:     B -- No --> D[Lock screen renders\\nPlan name, price, Subscribe CTA]\n355:     D --> E[Click Subscribe]\n356:     E --> F[Stripe Checkout session\\nfrappe/payments]\n357:     F --> G{Payment success?}\n358:     G -- No --> H[Error shown\\nRetry option]\n359:     G -- Yes --> I[Stripe webhook fires\\n/api/method/fg_companion.api.stripe_webhook]\n360:     I --> J[fg_paywall_grant row inserted\\nuser + space + plan]\n361:     J --> K[User redirected\\ninto Space within 5s]\n362:     K --> C\n363:     C --> L([Member can post, comment, react])\n364:     L --> M{Subscription lapses?}\n365:     M -- Yes --> N[Nightly job revokes grant\\nfg_paywall_grant deleted]\n366:     N --> O[User sees lock screen again\\non next visit]\n367:     M -- No --> L\n368: ```\n369: \n370: ### 5.9 Gamification & badge award\n371: \n372: ```mermaid\n373: flowchart TD\n374:     A([Member action occurs]) --> B{Action type}\n375:     B -- Post created --> C[EPS rule: +10 pts on first Post]\n376:     B -- Comment posted --> D[EPS rule: +5 pts]\n377:     B -- Course completed --> E[EPS rule: +100 pts]\n378:     B -- Mentor session done --> F[EPS rule: +50 pts for mentor]\n379:     C & D & E & F --> G[EPS Energy Point entry created\\nfrappe/eps]\n380:     G --> H[Check fg_badge thresholds]\n381:     H --> I{Threshold crossed?}\n382:     I -- No --> J([Points updated in profile])\n383:     I -- Yes --> K[fg_badge_award row created\\nuser + badge + awarded_at]\n384:     K --> L[Badge graphic shown\\nin profile Achievements section]\n385:     L --> M[Notification: 'You earned First Post badge']\n386:     M --> N([Profile updated])\n387: ```\n388: \n389: ### 5.10 Weekly community digest\n390: \n391: ```mermaid\n392: flowchart TD\n393:     A([Monday 08:00 scheduler fires]) --> B[fg_digest_job runs\\nfrappe scheduler_events]\n394:     B --> C[Query all users\\nwhere digest_opt_in = 1]\n395:     C --> D[For each user: fetch joined Spaces]\n396:     D --> E[Query last 7 days of posts\\nper Space ordered by reaction count]\n397:     E --> F[Top 3 posts per Space selected]\n398:     F --> G[Newsletter template rendered\\nwith signed unsubscribe token]\n399:     G --> H[frappe/newsletter send\\nEmail Queue populated]\n400:     H --> I[User receives email\\nsubject: 'This week in your spaces']\n401:     I --> J{User unsubscribes?}\n402:     J -- Yes --> K[digest_opt_in = 0\\nnever emailed again]\n403:     J -- No --> L([Next week's run])\n404: ```\n405: \n406: ### 5.11 Full platform data flow\n407: \n408: ```mermaid\n409: flowchart LR\n410:     subgraph Browser[\"Browser (React + TanStack Router)\"]\n411:         UI[Pages & Components]\n412:         TQ[TanStack Query cache]\n413:         UI <--> TQ\n414:     end\n415: \n416:     subgraph FrappeHTTP[\"Frappe HTTP API\"]\n417:         REST[\"/api/resource/…\\nCRUD\"]\n418:         RPC[\"/api/method/…\\nWhitelisted Python\"]\n419:     end\n420: \n421:     subgraph FrappeApps[\"Frappe Bench\"]\n422:         GP[gameplan\\nGP Discussion\\nGP Comment\\nGP Reaction]\n423:         LMS[lms\\nLMS Course\\nLMS Lesson\\nLMS Enrollment]\n424:         Raven[raven\\nRaven Channel\\nRaven Message]\n425:         FGC[fg_companion\\nFG Event\\nFG Mentor Match\\nFG AI Settings]\n426:         Core[frappe/frappe\\nUser, Role, Notification\\nEmail Queue, Job]\n427:     end\n428: \n429:     subgraph AI[\"AI / Workers\"]\n430:         Sent[Sentiment ONNX\\nbackground job]\n431:         Vec[pgvector\\nembeddings]\n432:         Otto[otto agent\\nAI bot]\n433:     end\n434: \n435:     TQ --> REST\n436:     TQ --> RPC\n437:     REST --> GP & LMS & Raven & FGC & Core\n438:     RPC --> FGC\n439:     GP --> Sent\n440:     GP --> Vec\n441:     Raven --> Otto\n442:     Core --> Email[\"Email Queue\\n(digest, events, alerts)\"]\n443:     Core --> Push[\"FCM Push\\n(mobile notifications)\"]\n444: ```\n445: \n446: ---\n447: \n448: ## 6. Project structure\n449: \n450: ```\n451: community-launchpad-proto/\n452: ├── src/\n453: │   ├── routes/                 # TanStack Router file-based pages\n454: │   │   ├── __root.tsx          # Shell: QueryClient, SplashScreen, Walkthrough\n455: │   │   ├── index.tsx           # Home feed (/)\n456: │   │   ├── spaces.$spaceId.tsx # Space detail\n457: │   │   ├── posts.$postId.tsx   # Post detail + comments\n458: │   │   ├── events.tsx          # Event grid + RSVP\n459: │   │   ├── mentors.tsx         # Mentor match flow\n460: │   │   ├── courses.tsx         # Course catalogue\n461: │   │   ├── courses.$courseId.tsx         # Course detail\n462: │   │   ├── courses.$courseId.lessons.$lessonId.tsx  # Lesson player\n463: │   │   ├── members.tsx         # Member directory\n464: │   │   ├── members.$userId.tsx # Member profile\n465: │   │   ├── messages.tsx        # DM thread list\n466: │   │   ├── messages.$threadId.tsx  # DM conversation\n467: │   │   ├── notifications.tsx   # Notification inbox\n468: │   │   ├── settings.tsx        # Full settings panel\n469: │   │   └── docs.tsx            # In-app docs\n470: │   │\n471: │   ├── components/\n472: │   │   ├── AppLayout.tsx       # Sidebar nav + top bar shell\n473: │   │   ├── PostCard.tsx        # Feed post card with reactions\n474: │   │   ├── SentimentBadge.tsx  # Amber \"Flagged\" badge (AI stub)\n475: │   │   ├── NewPostModal.tsx    # Rich post composer dialog\n476: │   │   ├── Avatar.tsx          # User avatar component\n477: │   │   ├── SplashScreen.tsx    # Animated first-load screen\n478: │   │   ├── Walkthrough.tsx     # First-time guided tour overlay\n479: │   │   └── ui/                 # shadcn/ui components (Radix-based)\n480: │   │\n481: │   ├── mock-data/\n482: │   │   ├── types.ts            # TypeScript shapes — mirror Frappe DocTypes\n483: │   │   ├── seed.ts             # Seeded fictional data (teams, spaces, posts…)\n484: │   │   └── store.ts            # Reactive in-memory store + mock AI functions\n485: │   │\n486: │   ├── hooks/                  # Custom React hooks\n487: │   ├── lib/                    # Utilities (cn, lovable-error-reporting…)\n488: │   ├── styles.css              # Tailwind + design tokens\n489: │   ├── router.tsx              # Router + QueryClient setup\n490: │   ├── server.ts               # Nitro SSR entry\n491: │   └── start.ts                # TanStack Start entry\n492: │\n493: ├── docs/\n494: │   ├── 00_OVERVIEW.md                   # This project at a glance\n495: │   ├── 01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md   # TS type ↔ Frappe DocType field table\n496: │   ├── 02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md       # What's fake; what's genuinely real\n497: │   ├── 03_PORTING_GUIDE.md              # High-level steps to production\n498: │   ├── 04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md         # Concrete Python, commands, code\n499: │   ├── 05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md   # Circle.so feature → Frappe mapping\n500: │   ├── 06_FRAPPE_ECOSYSTEM_TWIN.md      # App-by-app ecosystem breakdown\n501: │   ├── 07_ADR_001_FRAPPE_PLATFORM.md    # Original platform ADR\n502: │   ├── 08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md        # Gap matrix: ⭐ / 🟡 / 🔴 per feature\n503: │   ├── 09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md       # 12 Gherkin acceptance scenarios\n504: │   ├── 10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md        # How to adopt frappe-ui everywhere\n505: │   └── adr/\n506: │       ├── ADR-001-frappe-platform.md   # Platform choice\n507: │       ├── ADR-002-direct-messages-raven.md\n508: │       ├── ADR-003-live-events-teams-and-meet.md\n509: │       ├── ADR-004-member-directory-custom.md\n510: │       ├── ADR-005-paywall-gating-custom.md\n511: │       ├── ADR-006-moderation-custom.md\n512: │       ├── ADR-007-polls-custom.md\n513: │       ├── ADR-008-gamification-eps.md\n514: │       ├── ADR-009-mobile-strategy.md\n515: │       ├── ADR-010-ai-otto-raven-bot.md\n516: │       └── ADR-011-community-digest.md\n517: │\n518: ├── .lovable/\n519: │   ├── plan.md                 # Lovable project plan\n520: │   └── project.json\n521: ├── package.json\n522: ├── vite.config.ts\n523: ├── tsconfig.json\n524: ├── bunfig.toml\n525: └── README.md                   # You are here\n526: ```\n527: \n528: ---\n529: \n530: ## 7. Pages & routes\n531: \n532: | Route | File | Key components | Frappe target |\n533: |---|---|---|---|\n534: | `/` | `routes/index.tsx` | PostCard, SentimentBadge | `GP Discussion` list |\n535: | `/spaces/:spaceId` | `routes/spaces.$spaceId.tsx` | PostCard, NewPostModal | `GP Project` + `GP Discussion` filtered |\n536: | `/posts/:postId` | `routes/posts.$postId.tsx` | Comment thread, reactions, similar posts | `GP Discussion`, `GP Comment`, `GP Reaction` |\n537: | `/events` | `routes/events.tsx` | Event card grid, RSVP button | `FG Event`, `FG Event Attendee` |\n538: | `/mentors` | `routes/mentors.tsx` | Match request, match card | `FG Mentor Match` |\n539: | `/courses` | `routes/courses.tsx` | Course card grid | `LMS Course` |\n540: | `/courses/:courseId` | `routes/courses.$courseId.tsx` | Chapter list, lesson list, enrol | `LMS Course`, `LMS Chapter`, `LMS Enrollment` |\n541: | `/courses/:courseId/lessons/:lessonId` | `routes/courses.$courseId.lessons.$lessonId.tsx` | Lesson player, YouTube embed, progress | `LMS Lesson`, `LMS Course Progress` |\n542: | `/members` | `routes/members.tsx` | Filterable directory | `User` + `GP User Profile` |\n543: | `/members/:userId` | `routes/members.$userId.tsx` | Profile card, posts, badges | `GP User Profile` |\n544: | `/messages` | `routes/messages.tsx` | Thread list | `Raven Channel` |\n545: | `/messages/:threadId` | `routes/messages.$threadId.tsx` | Message bubbles, send form | `Raven Message` |\n546: | `/notifications` | `routes/notifications.tsx` | Notification inbox | `Notification Log` |\n547: | `/settings` | `routes/settings.tsx` | Notifications, Privacy, Integrations, AI, SSO | `FG User Settings`, `FG AI Settings`, `Social Login Key` |\n548: | `/docs` | `routes/docs.tsx` | In-app documentation panel | — |\n549: \n550: ---\n551: \n552: ## 8. Mock data & schema contract\n553: \n554: The file [`src/mock-data/types.ts`](src/mock-data/types.ts) is the **canonical schema contract** between the prototype and the production Frappe backend.\n555: \n556: Every TypeScript interface in that file mirrors a real Frappe DocType field-for-field, verified against the live `.json` files on the `main` branches of `frappe/gameplan` and `frappe/lms`. The mapping is fully documented in [`docs/01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md`](docs/01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md).\n557: \n558: ### DocTypes mirrored\n559: \n560: | TypeScript type | Frappe DocType | Source app |\n561: |---|---|---|\n562: | `GPTeam` | `GP Team` | frappe/gameplan |\n563: | `GPProject` | `GP Project` | frappe/gameplan |\n564: | `GPDiscussion` | `GP Discussion` | frappe/gameplan |\n565: | `GPComment` | `GP Comment` | frappe/gameplan |\n566: | `GPReaction` | `GP Reaction` | frappe/gameplan |\n567: | `GPUserProfile` | `GP User Profile` | frappe/gameplan |\n568: | `LMSCourse` | `LMS Course` | frappe/lms |\n569: | `LMSChapter` | `LMS Chapter` | frappe/lms |\n570: | `LMSLesson` | `LMS Lesson` | frappe/lms |\n571: | `LMSEnrollment` | `LMS Enrollment` | frappe/lms |\n572: | `LMSCourseProgress` | `LMS Course Progress` | frappe/lms |\n573: | `FGEvent` | `FG Event` | fg_companion (new) |\n574: | `FGEventAttendee` | `FG Event Attendee` | fg_companion (new) |\n575: | `FGMentorMatch` | `FG Mentor Match` | fg_companion (new) |\n576: | `FGAISettings` | `FG AI Settings` | fg_companion (new) |\n577: | `FGUserSettings` | `FG User Settings` | fg_companion (new) |\n578: | `FGDMThread` | `Raven Channel` | frappe/raven |\n579: | `FGDMMessage` | `Raven Message` | frappe/raven |\n580: | `FGNotification` | `Notification Log` | frappe/frappe core |\n581: | `FGSSOProvider` | `Social Login Key` | frappe/frappe core |\n582: \n583: ### What is genuinely real vs mocked\n584: \n585: **Real** (actually mutates state in-memory):\n586: - Creating posts, posting comments, RSVPing to events, requesting mentor matches\n587: - All navigation, URL routing, page composition\n588: - The schema — all TypeScript shapes match real Frappe\n589: \n590: **Mocked** (keyword stubs, not ML):\n591: - `mockSentiment()` in `store.ts` — keyword scorer, not ONNX\n592: - `findSimilarPosts()` in `store.ts` — word-overlap, not pgvector\n593: - Auth — the \"current user\" is hardcoded to `maya` in the store\n594: \n595: See [`docs/02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md`](docs/02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md) for full detail.\n596: \n597: ---\n598: \n599: ## 9. The Frappe DNA — why this stack\n600: \n601: This platform is built on the Frappe Framework. This is a deliberate, reasoned decision documented fully in [`docs/adr/ADR-001-frappe-platform.md`](docs/adr/ADR-001-frappe-platform.md). Key reasons:\n602: \n603: ### 1. One auth, one user, one permission model\n604: Every surface — community posts, courses, DMs, helpdesk tickets, wiki pages — uses the **same `User` row, the same Role system, the same DocPerm model**. No SSO duct tape, no role-sync jobs, no cross-system identity drift.\n605: \n606: ### 2. Data sovereignty\n607: First-generation students are a vulnerable cohort. Their data lives in a single Postgres database on UK-region infrastructure (Civo, Hetzner-eu, AWS eu-west-2). `bench backup` creates a complete dump as one tarball. No vendor is in the data path.\n608: \n609: ### 3. Cost at scale\n610: At 5,000 members, Circle.so Pro is ~6× the cost of self-hosted Frappe. The Frappe stack is open source end-to-end and cost scales with infrastructure, not seats.\n611: \n612: ### 4. Extensibility without forking\n613: All extension of upstream apps (gameplan, lms, raven) happens via:\n614: - **Custom Fields** added from `fg_companion` fixtures\n615: - **`doc_events`** hooks in `fg_companion/hooks.py`\n616: - **New DocTypes** in `fg_companion` only\n617: \n618: No upstream app is ever forked. `bench update` continues to work.\n619: \n620: ### 5. The Circle.so feature map is complete\n621: Every Circle.so feature has a Frappe equivalent. See [`docs/05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md`](docs/05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md) and the gap analysis in [`docs/08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md`](docs/08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md).\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## 10. The Circle.so DNA — feature parity map\n626: \n627: | Circle.so feature | Frappe equivalent | Status |\n628: |---|---|---|\n629: | Community / site | Frappe site | ⭐ |\n630: | Space Group | `GP Team` | ⭐ |\n631: | Space | `GP Project` | ⭐ |\n632: | Post | `GP Discussion` | ⭐ |\n633: | Comment | `GP Comment` | ⭐ |\n634: | Emoji reaction | `GP Reaction` | ⭐ |\n635: | Member directory | Custom `fg_member_directory` | 🔨 Build |\n636: | Member profile | `GP User Profile` | ⭐ |\n637: | DMs / Channels | Raven | ⭐ |\n638: | Notifications | Frappe `Notification Log` | ⭐ |\n639: | Search | Frappe FTS5 global search | ⭐ |\n640: | Courses | `frappe/lms` full stack | ⭐ |\n641: | Live events (Teams) | `fg_live_event` + Microsoft Graph | 🔨 Build |\n642: | Live events (internal) | `frappe/meet` WebRTC | 🟡 |\n643: | Polls | `fg_poll` + `fg_poll_vote` | 🔨 Build |\n644: | Paywall / membership | `frappe/payments` + `fg_paywall_grant` | 🟡 |\n645: | Email digest | `frappe/newsletter` + `fg_digest_job` | 🟡 |\n646: | Gamification | `frappe/eps` + `fg_badge` | ⭐ |\n647: | Helpdesk / support | `frappe/helpdesk` | ⭐ |\n648: | Wiki / handbook | `frappe/wiki` | ⭐ |\n649: | Analytics | `frappe/insights` | ⭐ |\n650: | AI moderation | `fg_companion` + ONNX sentiment | 🔨 Build |\n651: | AI bot | Raven AI bot / otto | 🟡 |\n652: | Mobile | Raven mobile + PWA | 🟡 |\n653: | SSO / OAuth2 | Frappe Social Login Key | ⭐ |\n654: | 2FA | Frappe TOTP / Email OTP | ⭐ |\n655: \n656: *⭐ = production-ready Frappe feature · 🟡 = partial/early · 🔨 = build in `fg_companion`*\n657: \n658: ---\n659: \n660: ## 11. Documentation index\n661: \n662: | Document | Purpose |\n663: |---|---|\n664: | [`docs/00_OVERVIEW.md`](docs/00_OVERVIEW.md) | Project at a glance |\n665: | [`docs/01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md`](docs/01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md) | Field-by-field TS ↔ DocType table |\n666: | [`docs/02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md`](docs/02_WHATS_MOCKED_VS_REAL.md) | What's fake vs genuinely real |\n667: | [`docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md`](docs/03_PORTING_GUIDE.md) | High-level 6-step porting recipe |\n668: | [`docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md`](docs/04_FRAPPE_TRANSLATION.md) | Concrete Python, shell commands, code samples |\n669: | [`docs/05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md`](docs/05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md) | Circle feature → DocType table |\n670: | [`docs/06_FRAPPE_ECOSYSTEM_TWIN.md`](docs/06_FRAPPE_ECOSYSTEM_TWIN.md) | App-by-app ecosystem breakdown |\n671: | [`docs/07_ADR_001_FRAPPE_PLATFORM.md`](docs/07_ADR_001_FRAPPE_PLATFORM.md) | Platform ADR (backward-compat copy) |\n672: | [`docs/08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md`](docs/08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md) | Gap matrix per feature |\n673: | [`docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md`](docs/09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md) | 12 acceptance scenarios |\n674: | [`docs/10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md`](docs/10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md) | Adopting frappe-ui component library |\n675: | [`docs/adr/ADR-001`](docs/adr/ADR-001-frappe-platform.md) through [`ADR-011`](docs/adr/ADR-011-community-digest.md) | All architecture decisions |\n676: \n677: ---\n678: \n679: ## 12. How long to production?\n680: \n681: See [`docs/10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md`](docs/10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md) for the full build estimate. Summary:\n682: \n683: ### Phase 0 — Infrastructure (Week 1–2)\n684: - Provision Frappe bench on UK-region server\n685: - Install gameplan, lms, raven, helpdesk, wiki, insights, eps, newsletter\n686: - Create `fg_companion` app skeleton + fixtures\n687: - Set up CI/CD (GitHub Actions → staging bench)\n688: \n689: **Deliverable:** live staging site, all upstream apps installed, empty data\n690: \n691: ### Phase 1 — Data layer swap (Week 3–4)\n692: - Replace `src/mock-data/store.ts` with `src/data/store.ts` (Frappe HTTP client)\n693: - Wire real Frappe auth (session cookie + CSRF token)\n694: - Seed staging with real-looking data\n695: \n696: **Deliverable:** prototype talks to real Frappe; all CRUD works end-to-end\n697: \n698: ### Phase 2 — fg_companion DocTypes (Week 5–6)\n699: - FG Event, FG Event Attendee, FG Mentor Match, FG User Settings, FG AI Settings\n700: - Custom Fields: `fg_sentiment_label`, `fg_sentiment_score`, `fg_embedding`, `fg_reviewed_by`\n701: - RPC endpoints: `rsvp()`, `request_mentor()`, `ics_export()`\n702: \n703: **Deliverable:** events, RSVP, mentor match, settings all backed by real DocTypes\n704: \n705: ### Phase 3 — AI features (Week 7–8)\n706: - Sentiment ONNX model in background worker (real, not keyword)\n707: - pgvector for similar discussions (real embeddings)\n708: - Moderation queue wired to Helpdesk\n709: - Safeguarding DM via Raven on sentiment flag\n710: \n711: **Deliverable:** real AI moderation, real vector search\n712: \n713: ### Phase 4 — Build-from-scratch features (Week 9–12)\n714: - Member directory (filterable, opt-in/out)\n715: - Polls (`fg_poll`, `fg_poll_vote`, feed card)\n716: - Gamification visuals (`fg_badge`, `fg_badge_award`)\n717: - Paywall (`fg_paywall_grant`, Stripe webhook, lock screen)\n718: - Community digest (`fg_digest_job`, Newsletter template)\n719: - Microsoft Teams live events (Graph API Server Script)\n720: \n721: **Deliverable:** full Circle.so feature parity\n722: \n723: ### Phase 5 — frappe-ui migration (Week 13–14)\n724: - Swap shadcn/ui components for frappe-ui equivalents\n725: - Apply Frappe design tokens\n726: - Verify WCAG 2.2 AA\n727: \n728: **Deliverable:** unified Frappe design system throughout\n729: \n730: ### Phase 6 — QA, pen-test, go-live (Week 15–16)\n731: - Full Gherkin scenario test pass\n732: - Pen-test fg_companion whitelisted endpoints\n733: - WCAG audit\n734: - Go-live\n735: \n736: ### Total estimate: **14–16 weeks** (one senior full-stack engineer + one Frappe Python developer)\n737: \n738: > If the team already has Frappe experience, Phase 0–2 compress to 3 weeks. The bottleneck is Phase 4 (build-from-scratch features).\n739: \n740: ---\n741: \n742: ## 13. Contributing & branch rules\n743: \n744: This repository is connected to [Lovable](https://lovable.dev). Please **do not** force-push, rebase, amend, or squash commits that have already been pushed — this rewrites history on Lovable's side and will cause the user to lose their project history.\n745: \n746: All commits to the connected branch sync back to Lovable and show up in the editor, so keep the branch in a working state at all times.\n747: \n748: ### Development workflow\n749: \n750: ```bash\n751: # Work on a feature branch\n752: git checkout -b feat/my-feature\n753: \n754: # Make changes, then commit\n755: git add .\n756: git commit -m \"feat: add mentor match request flow\"\n757: \n758: # Push and open a PR\n759: git push origin feat/my-feature\n760: ```\n761: \n762: ### Commit convention\n763: \n764: We use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):\n765: \n766: ```\n767: feat:     new feature or UX flow\n768: fix:      bug fix in prototype behaviour\n769: docs:     documentation only change\n770: style:    formatting, no logic change\n771: refactor: code change that neither fixes nor adds\n772: test:     add or update tests\n773: chore:    build system, tooling\n774: ```\n775: \n776: ---\n777: \n778: *Built with ❤️ for first-generation university students everywhere.*\n779: *Prototype: React + TanStack + Tailwind. Production target: Frappe Framework.*\n\n(End of file - total 779 lines)\n</content>",
