      "type": "action",
      "tool": "edit",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\community-launchpad-proto\\\\README.md\", \"newString\": \"### Prerequisites\\n\\n| Tool | Minimum version | Check |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| [Node.js](https://nodejs.org) | 20 LTS | `node -v` |\\n| Git | any recent | `git --version` |\\n\\n### Clone & install\\n\\n```bash\\ngit clone https://github.com/andiekobbietks/community-launchpad-proto.git\\ncd community-launchpad-proto\\nnpm install\\n```\\n\\n### Start the dev server\\n\\n```bash\\nnpm run dev\\n```\\n\\nOpen [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080). Hot-module replacement is enabled \\u2014 file saves are reflected instantly.\\n\\n### Available scripts\\n\\n| Script | What it does |\\n|---|---|\\n| `npm run dev` | Starts Vite dev server with HMR on port 8080 |\\n| `npm run build` | Production build |\\n| `npm run build:dev` | Dev-mode build (useful for debugging) |\\n| `npm run preview` | Serves the production build locally |\\n| `npm run lint` | ESLint across all TypeScript/Vue files |\\n| `npm run format` | Prettier format all files |\", \"oldString\": \"### Prerequisites\\n\\n| Tool | Minimum version | Check |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| [Node.js](https://nodejs.org) | 20 LTS | `node -v` |\\n| [Bun](https://bun.sh) | 1.1+ | `bun -v` |\\n| Git | any recent | `git --version` |\\n\\n> **Windows note:** Bun runs natively on Windows. All commands below work in PowerShell, CMD, or Git Bash.\\n\\n### Clone & install\\n\\n```bash\\ngit clone https://github.com/andiekobbietks/community-launchpad-proto.git\\ncd community-launchpad-proto\\nbun install\\n```\\n\\n### Start the dev server\\n\\n```bash\\nbun run dev\\n```\\n\\nOpen [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000). Hot-module replacement is enabled \\u2014 file saves are reflected instantly.\\n\\n### Available scripts\\n\\n| Script | What it does |\\n|---|---|\\n| `bun run dev` | Starts Vite dev server with HMR on port 3000 |\\n| `bun run build` | Production build (Nitro SSR bundle + static assets) |\\n| `bun run build:dev` | Dev-mode build (useful for debugging) |\\n| `bun run preview` | Serves the production build locally |\\n| `bun run lint` | ESLint across all TypeScript/React files |\\n| `bun run format` | Prettier format all files |\"}",
