      "text": "Fixed. The problem was **Tailwind CSS v4 requires the `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin** — it was missing from both `package.json` and `vite.config.ts`.\n\n**What was wrong:** Without the Vite plugin, none of the Tailwind CSS was being processed. The `@import \"tailwindcss\"` in `styles.css` and all the utility classes in the `.vue` files were ignored, resulting in raw unstyled HTML.\n\n**What I fixed:**\n1. Installed `@tailwindcss/vite` \n2. Added `tailwindcss()` plugin to `vite.config.ts` (before the Vue plugin)\n3. Restarted the server\n\nRefresh Edge at **http://localhost:8080** — you should see the fully styled Circle.so-like UI now with the sidebar, top nav, cards, and violet accent.",
