      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto\\docs\\09_GHERKIN_UX_SCENARIOS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # 09 — Gherkin UX Scenarios\n2: \n3: One scenario per feature area. Each is signed by **Circle source of inspiration** + **Frappe implementation** + **custom glue** so QA can validate UX independently of the eventual port.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## 1. Direct messages (Raven)\n8: \n9: ```gherkin\n10: Feature: Direct messages between mentors and mentees\n11:   Source: Circle DMs\n12:   Frappe: Raven channels + DM\n13:   Glue: fg_mentor_match.on_accept hook creates a Raven DM channel\n14: \n15:   Scenario: Mentor opens a 1:1 thread with a matched mentee\n16:     Given Maya is signed in as a verified mentor\n17:     And she has an accepted mentor match with Joel\n18:     When she clicks \"Message Joel\" from the match card\n19:     Then a Raven DM channel opens with Joel as the only other member\n20:     And the first system message reads \"Match accepted on <date>\"\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ## 2. Live events — Microsoft Teams\n24: \n25: ```gherkin\n26: Feature: Hosting a cross-org Q&A on Microsoft Teams\n27:   Source: Circle Live\n28:   Frappe: fg_live_event DocType + Microsoft Graph Server Script\n29:   Glue: Admin completes Azure App Registration steps shown in Settings → Integrations → Microsoft Teams\n30: \n31:   Scenario: Admin creates a Teams event from the Events page\n32:     Given an admin with Microsoft Teams credentials configured\n33:     When they click \"New event\" and select provider \"Microsoft Teams\"\n34:     And submit title \"Personal statement clinic\" with date next Tuesday 18:00\n35:     Then a new fg_live_event row is created with provider = \"teams\"\n36:     And a Microsoft Graph call to /me/onlineMeetings returns a join_url\n37:     And the event card shows a \"Join on Teams\" button to all members of the host Space\n38:     And an .ics file is attached to the confirmation email\n39: ```\n40: \n41: ## 3. Live events — frappe/meet (internal)\n42: \n43: ```gherkin\n44: Feature: Quick internal video room for a mentor group\n45:   Source: Circle Live (rooms)\n46:   Frappe: frappe/meet (WebRTC)\n47:   Glue: fg_live_event with provider = \"meet\"\n48: \n49:   Scenario: Mentor spins up an instant room\n50:     Given a mentor in the \"Mentor Lounge\" space\n51:     When they click \"Start room\"\n52:     Then a frappe/meet room is created and they join as host\n53:     And other space members see a live banner \"Mentor Lounge is live now\"\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ## 4. Member directory\n57: \n58: ```gherkin\n59: Feature: Finding a peer with shared experience\n60:   Source: Circle Members\n61:   Frappe: custom fg_member_directory + Framework Report Builder\n62:   Glue: profile_public flag on User; filterable list view\n63: \n64:   Scenario: First-gen student filters mentors by course and region\n65:     Given Joel is signed in as a first-year student\n66:     When he opens \"Members\" and filters skills = \"Law\", region = \"North West\"\n67:     Then only members with profile_public = 1 and matching tags appear\n68:     And each card shows year-group, course, \"Message\" and \"Request mentor match\" buttons\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ## 5. Paywall / membership gating\n72: \n73: ```gherkin\n74: Feature: Locking a premium Space behind a subscription\n75:   Source: Circle Paywalls\n76:   Frappe: frappe/payments + ERPNext Subscription + fg_paywall_grant\n77:   Glue: fg_space.paywall_plan; on subscription.active → grant; on lapse → revoke\n78: \n79:   Scenario: Visitor tries to enter a paid Space\n80:     Given a Space \"UCAS Premium\" with paywall_plan = \"fg-prem-monthly\"\n81:     And Visitor Sam is not subscribed\n82:     When Sam clicks the space in the sidebar\n83:     Then a lock screen appears with the plan name, price and \"Subscribe\" CTA\n84:     And on successful Stripe checkout a fg_paywall_grant row is written\n85:     And Sam is redirected into the space within 5 seconds\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ## 6. Moderation queue\n89: \n90: ```gherkin\n91: Feature: Auto-flagging a post that breaks the rules\n92:   Source: Circle Moderation\n93:   Frappe: custom fg_moderation_rule + fg_moderation_queue + Helpdesk for appeals\n94:   Glue: on Post.before_insert run regex + AI sentiment from Lovable AI\n95: \n96:   Scenario: A post containing a blocked term is held for review\n97:     Given a moderation rule with regex \"(?i)\\b(scam|kys)\\b\" and action = \"hold\"\n98:     When a member submits a post containing \"kys\"\n99:     Then the post is created with status = \"held\"\n100:     And a fg_moderation_queue row is created assigned to role \"Trusted Reviewer\"\n101:     And the author sees a banner \"Your post is awaiting review\"\n102:     And reviewers see the item in the queue with Approve / Reject / Edit actions\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## 7. Polls\n106: \n107: ```gherkin\n108: Feature: Polling a space about study preferences\n109:   Source: Circle Polls\n110:   Frappe: custom fg_poll + fg_poll_vote\n111:   Glue: poll card rendered inline in feed; one vote per user per poll\n112: \n113:   Scenario: Member votes on an embedded poll\n114:     Given a feed post with an attached fg_poll \"Best revision time?\" with options Morning/Evening/Night\n115:     When Maya selects \"Evening\" and clicks Vote\n116:     Then a fg_poll_vote row is written for (maya, poll, \"Evening\")\n117:     And the card re-renders to show percentages and total votes\n118:     And the Vote button is replaced with \"You voted: Evening\"\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ## 8. Gamification (EPS + visual badges)\n122: \n123: ```gherkin\n124: Feature: Earning a \"First Post\" badge\n125:   Source: Circle Gamification\n126:   Frappe: frappe/eps for points + custom fg_badge for visuals\n127:   Glue: EPS rule grants 10 pts on first Post; fg_badge_award on threshold\n128: \n129:   Scenario: New member's first post awards a badge\n130:     Given Joel has zero EPS points and no badges\n131:     When he publishes his first post in \"First Year Support\"\n132:     Then his EPS balance increases by 10\n133:     And a fg_badge_award row is created linking him to badge \"First Post\"\n134:     And his profile shows the badge graphic in the Achievements section\n135: ```\n136: \n137: ## 9. Mobile\n138: \n139: ```gherkin\n140: Feature: Receiving a DM notification on mobile\n141:   Source: Circle mobile app\n142:   Frappe: Raven React Native app + Framework FCM\n143:   Glue: Push token registered on login\n144: \n145:   Scenario: Push lands while app is closed\n146:     Given Maya has the Raven mobile app installed and is signed in\n147:     When another member sends her a DM\n148:     Then within 5 seconds her device shows a push notification with the sender name\n149:     And tapping the notification deep-links to the DM thread\n150: ```\n151: \n152: ## 10. AI assistance (Raven bot / otto)\n153: \n154: ```gherkin\n155: Feature: Asking the community AI bot a UCAS question\n156:   Source: Circle AI\n157:   Frappe: Raven AI bot (OpenAI/Anthropic) or otto agent\n158:   Glue: bot has read access to frappe/wiki \"UCAS handbook\"\n159: \n160:   Scenario: Member asks the bot in #help\n161:     Given the channel #help has the FG AI bot installed\n162:     When a member writes \"@FGBot what's the UCAS deadline for medicine?\"\n163:     Then the bot replies within 10 seconds quoting the Wiki page \"ucas/deadlines\"\n164:     And the reply contains a link to the source wiki page\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ## 11. Community digest\n168: \n169: ```gherkin\n170: Feature: Weekly \"what you missed\" email\n171:   Source: Circle weekly digest\n172:   Frappe: frappe/newsletter + custom fg_digest_job\n173:   Glue: scheduled Monday 08:00; query last 7 days of joined spaces\n174: \n175:   Scenario: Active member gets a personalised digest\n176:     Given Maya is a member of \"First Year Support\" and \"Mentor Lounge\"\n177:     And digest_opt_in = 1\n178:     When the Monday 08:00 scheduler runs\n179:     Then she receives an email subject \"This week in your spaces\"\n180:     And the email lists the top 3 posts per space by reaction count\n181:     And every link is signed with her unsubscribe token\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ## 12. Cross-space activity feed\n185: \n186: ```gherkin\n187: Feature: Home feed aggregates across joined spaces\n188:   Source: Circle home feed\n189:   Frappe: custom view over Post + fg_space_membership\n190:   Glue: ranking = recency * (1 + log(reactions))\n191: \n192:   Scenario: Member opens the home page\n193:     Given Joel has joined two spaces with new activity today\n194:     When he loads \"/\"\n195:     Then posts from both spaces appear interleaved by rank\n196:     And each card shows its space name and a \"Mute this space\" overflow action\n197: ```\n\n(End of file - total 197 lines)\n</content>",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1781947612750
    },
