      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\community-launchpad-proto\\\\docs\\\\10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md\"}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto\\docs\\10_FRAPPE_UI_MIGRATION.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # 10 — Frappe UI Migration Guide\n2: \n3: > **What this document covers:** How to migrate the FirstGens Community prototype\n4: > from its current stack (shadcn/ui + Radix primitives + Tailwind) to\n5: > [`frappe-ui`](https://github.com/frappe/frappe-ui) — the component library\n6: > and design system used across all official Frappe applications (Gameplan,\n7: > LMS, Raven, Helpdesk, Desk, etc.). After this migration the React shell and\n8: > every Frappe app share one design language.\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## Why frappe-ui?\n13: \n14: | Today (prototype) | After migration |\n15: |---|---|\n16: | shadcn/ui + Radix | frappe-ui + Radix (same primitives under the hood) |\n17: | Tailwind CSS 4 custom tokens | Frappe design tokens (`ink-gray-*`, `surface-*`, etc.) |\n18: | Ad-hoc component composition | Battle-tested components from every Frappe product |\n19: | Custom Button, Input, Dialog, Tabs… | `<Button>`, `<TextInput>`, `<Dialog>`, `<Tabs>` from frappe-ui |\n20: | No built-in Frappe API helpers | `createResource`, `createListResource`, real-time sockets |\n21: \n22: The biggest win: frappe-ui ships **`createResource`** and **`createListResource`** — reactive wrappers around `frappe.client` that replace the prototype's entire `src/mock-data/store.ts` with a few lines of declarative code. They handle loading states, pagination, caching, and Frappe's CSRF token automatically.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## Installation\n27: \n28: frappe-ui is a **Vue 3 library** for Frappe Desk apps. However, the FirstGens React shell does not run inside Frappe Desk — it is a standalone React SPA that talks to Frappe's REST API. This means:\n29: \n30: 1. **You cannot use frappe-ui's Vue components directly in the React shell.**\n31: 2. **You CAN use frappe-ui's design tokens, CSS variables, and Tailwind preset** — and adopt the same visual design system.\n32: 3. **You CAN use frappe-ui's `frappe-ui` npm package as a reference** for design decisions and then build equivalent React wrappers.\n33: 4. **If you later migrate the shell to Vue 3**, frappe-ui becomes a drop-in.\n34: \n35: ### Option A — React shell + frappe-ui design tokens (recommended short-term)\n36: \n37: Install frappe-ui in the project purely to inherit its CSS custom properties and Tailwind config:\n38: \n39: ```bash\n40: bun add frappe-ui\n41: ```\n42: \n43: Then in `src/styles.css`:\n44: \n45: ```css\n46: /* Import frappe-ui base CSS (design tokens + reset) */\n47: @import \"frappe-ui/dist/frappe-ui.css\";\n48: \n49: /* Keep existing Tailwind directives */\n50: @tailwind base;\n51: @tailwind components;\n52: @tailwind utilities;\n53: ```\n54: \n55: In `tailwind.config.ts`:\n56: \n57: ```ts\n58: import frappeUiPreset from \"frappe-ui/src/utils/tailwind.config\";\n59: \n60: export default {\n61:   presets: [frappeUiPreset],\n62:   content: [\n63:     \"./src/**/*.{ts,tsx}\",\n64:     // Include frappe-ui components so Tailwind picks up their classes\n65:     \"./node_modules/frappe-ui/src/components/**/*.{vue,js}\",\n66:   ],\n67: };\n68: ```\n69: \n70: This gives you the full Frappe colour palette, spacing, and typography tokens immediately, with zero component rewrites.\n71: \n72: ### Option B — Full Vue 3 migration (recommended for production)\n73: \n74: When the production port moves to Frappe, migrate the React shell to Vue 3 so frappe-ui components can be used natively. The TanStack Router is replaced by Vue Router (which Gameplan already uses).\n75: \n76: ```bash\n77: # In the production fg_companion frontend:\n78: bun add frappe-ui @vueuse/core vue-router\n79: ```\n80: \n81: Import components:\n82: \n83: ```vue\n84: <script setup lang=\"ts\">\n85: import { Button, TextInput, Dialog, ListView, Tabs } from \"frappe-ui\";\n86: </script>\n87: \n88: <template>\n89:   <Button variant=\"solid\" @click=\"submit\">Post</Button>\n90: </template>\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## Design token mapping\n96: \n97: The table below maps every custom CSS variable currently used in `src/styles.css` to its frappe-ui equivalent. After installing frappe-ui you can do a project-wide find-and-replace.\n98: \n99: ### Colours\n100: \n101: | Current token | frappe-ui token | Notes |\n102: |---|---|---|\n103: | `--background` | `--surface-base` | Page background |\n104: | `--foreground` | `--ink-base` | Primary text |\n105: | `--muted` | `--surface-gray-2` | Muted surfaces |\n106: | `--muted-foreground` | `--ink-gray-5` | Secondary text |\n107: | `--border` | `--outline-gray-2` | Default border |\n108: | `--input` | `--surface-gray-2` | Input background |\n109: | `--ring` | `--outline-gray-4` | Focus ring |\n110: | `--primary` | `--surface-gray-10` | Primary action |\n111: | `--primary-foreground` | `--ink-base` | Text on primary |\n112: | `--secondary` | `--surface-gray-3` | Secondary button |\n113: | `--destructive` | `--surface-red-2` | Danger |\n114: | `--destructive-foreground` | `--ink-red` | Danger text |\n115: | `--accent` | `--surface-gray-2` | Hover accent |\n116: | `--accent-foreground` | `--ink-gray-8` | Accent text |\n117: | `--card` | `--surface-base` | Card background |\n118: | `--card-foreground` | `--ink-base` | Card text |\n119: | `--popover` | `--surface-base` | Popover background |\n120: | `--popover-foreground` | `--ink-base` | Popover text |\n121: \n122: ### Typography\n123: \n124: | Current | frappe-ui class | Notes |\n125: |---|---|---|\n126: | `text-sm font-medium` | `text-p-sm-medium` | Small medium body |\n127: | `text-base` | `text-p-base` | Base body text |\n128: | `text-lg` | `text-p-lg` | Large body text |\n129: | `font-semibold text-xl` | `text-h3` | Heading 3 |\n130: | `font-bold text-2xl` | `text-h2` | Heading 2 |\n131: | `font-bold text-3xl` | `text-h1` | Heading 1 |\n132: \n133: ### Spacing, radius, shadows\n134: \n135: frappe-ui uses the same Tailwind spacing scale. Radius and shadows use tokens:\n136: \n137: | Need | frappe-ui token |\n138: |---|---|\n139: | `rounded-md` | `rounded` (4px base) |\n140: | `rounded-lg` | `rounded-lg` (8px) |\n141: | `shadow-sm` | `shadow-sm` |\n142: | `ring-1` focus | `focus-ring` utility class |\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Component-by-component migration plan\n147: \n148: ### Buttons\n149: \n150: **Before (shadcn/ui):**\n151: ```tsx\n152: import { Button } from \"@/components/ui/button\";\n153: \n154: <Button variant=\"default\" size=\"sm\" onClick={handleClick}>\n155:   RSVP\n156: </Button>\n157: ```\n158: \n159: **After (frappe-ui React wrapper or Vue):**\n160: ```vue\n161: <!-- Vue (production Frappe shell) -->\n162: <Button variant=\"solid\" size=\"sm\" @click=\"handleRsvp\">RSVP</Button>\n163: ```\n164: \n165: ```tsx\n166: // React interim — wrap frappe-ui tokens in a thin shim:\n167: // src/components/ui/fg-button.tsx\n168: export function FGButton({ variant = \"solid\", size = \"sm\", ...props }) {\n169:   const base = \"inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 transition-colors shrink-0 rounded\";\n170:   const variants = {\n171:     solid: \"bg-surface-gray-10 text-ink-base hover:bg-surface-gray-9\",\n172:     subtle: \"bg-surface-gray-2 text-ink-gray-8 hover:bg-surface-gray-3\",\n173:     ghost: \"text-ink-gray-8 hover:bg-surface-gray-2\",\n174:     danger: \"bg-surface-red-2 text-ink-red hover:bg-surface-red-3\",\n175:   };\n176:   const sizes = {\n177:     xs: \"h-6 px-2 text-xs\",\n178:     sm: \"h-7 px-2 text-sm\",\n179:     md: \"h-8 px-3 text-base\",\n180:     lg: \"h-9 px-4 text-base\",\n181:   };\n182:   return <button className={`${base} ${variants[variant]} ${sizes[size]}`} {...props} />;\n183: }\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ### Text inputs\n187: \n188: **Before (shadcn/ui):**\n189: ```tsx\n190: import { Input } from \"@/components/ui/input\";\n191: \n192: <Input placeholder=\"Search members…\" value={q} onChange={e => setQ(e.target.value)} />\n193: ```\n194: \n195: **After (frappe-ui tokens):**\n196: ```tsx\n197: // React shim:\n198: <input\n199:   className=\"text-base rounded h-7 py-1.5 px-2\n200:              border border-[--surface-gray-2] bg-surface-gray-2\n201:              placeholder-ink-gray-4\n202:              hover:border-outline-elevation-2 hover:bg-surface-gray-3\n203:              focus:bg-surface-base focus:border-outline-gray-4\n204:              focus:shadow-sm focus:ring-0\n205:              text-ink-gray-8 transition-colors w-full\"\n206:   placeholder=\"Search members…\"\n207:   value={q}\n208:   onChange={e => setQ(e.target.value)}\n209: />\n210: ```\n211: \n212: ### Dialogs / modals\n213: \n214: frappe-ui's `<Dialog>` uses Headless UI under the hood. The React equivalent:\n215: \n216: ```tsx\n217: // Keep using Radix Dialog but apply frappe-ui tokens:\n218: import * as RadixDialog from \"@radix-ui/react-dialog\";\n219: \n220: function FGDialog({ children, title }) {\n221:   return (\n222:     <RadixDialog.Root>\n223:       <RadixDialog.Portal>\n224:         <RadixDialog.Overlay className=\"fixed inset-0 bg-ink-base/30 backdrop-blur-sm\" />\n225:         <RadixDialog.Content\n226:           className=\"fixed top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2\n227:                      bg-surface-base rounded-lg shadow-2xl border border-outline-gray-1\n228:                      p-5 w-full max-w-lg max-h-[85vh] overflow-auto\"\n229:         >\n230:           <RadixDialog.Title className=\"text-h3 text-ink-base mb-4\">{title}</RadixDialog.Title>\n231:           {children}\n232:         </RadixDialog.Content>\n233:       </RadixDialog.Portal>\n234:     </RadixDialog.Root>\n235:   );\n236: }\n237: ```\n238: \n239: ### Tabs\n240: \n241: frappe-ui's `<Tabs>` is a thin wrapper around native browser tabs. React equivalent:\n242: \n243: ```tsx\n244: // src/components/ui/fg-tabs.tsx\n245: interface Tab { id: string; label: string }\n246: \n247: function FGTabs({ tabs, active, onChange }: { tabs: Tab[]; active: string; onChange: (id: string) => void }) {\n248:   return (\n249:     <div className=\"flex gap-1 border-b border-outline-gray-1 mb-4\">\n250:       {tabs.map(t => (\n251:         <button\n252:           key={t.id}\n253:           onClick={() => onChange(t.id)}\n254:           className={`px-3 py-2 text-p-sm-medium transition-colors border-b-2 -mb-px\n255:             ${active === t.id\n256:               ? \"border-ink-gray-9 text-ink-gray-9\"\n257:               : \"border-transparent text-ink-gray-5 hover:text-ink-gray-7\"}`}\n258:         >\n259:           {t.label}\n260:         </button>\n261:       ))}\n262:     </div>\n263:   );\n264: }\n265: ```\n266: \n267: ### ListView (frappe-ui's killer feature)\n268: \n269: frappe-ui ships `<ListView>` — a virtualised, Frappe-aware list component. In Vue:\n270: \n271: ```vue\n272: <template>\n273:   <ListView\n274:     :columns=\"columns\"\n275:     :rows=\"discussions.data\"\n276:     :options=\"{ selectable: true, showTooltip: true }\"\n277:     row-key=\"name\"\n278:     @row-click=\"openDiscussion\"\n279:   />\n280: </template>\n281: \n282: <script setup>\n283: import { createListResource, ListView } from \"frappe-ui\";\n284: \n285: const discussions = createListResource({\n286:   doctype: \"GP Discussion\",\n287:   fields: [\"name\", \"title\", \"content\", \"last_post_at\", \"comments_count\"],\n288:   filters: { project: props.spaceId },\n289:   orderBy: \"last_post_at desc\",\n290:   pageLength: 20,\n291:   auto: true,\n292: });\n293: </script>\n294: ```\n295: \n296: React interim — render manually using the fetched data:\n297: \n298: ```tsx\n299: // src/data/useDiscussions.ts\n300: import { useQuery } from \"@tanstack/react-query\";\n301: \n302: export function useDiscussions(spaceId?: string) {\n303:   return useQuery({\n304:     queryKey: [\"discussions\", spaceId],\n305:     queryFn: async () => {\n306:       const filters = spaceId ? `[[\"project\",\"=\",\"${spaceId}\"]]` : \"[]\";\n307:       const res = await fetch(\n308:         `/api/resource/GP Discussion?fields=[\"name\",\"title\",\"content\",\"last_post_at\",\"comments_count\",\"owner\",\"creation\"]&filters=${filters}&order_by=last_post_at+desc&limit_page_length=20`,\n309:         { credentials: \"include\" }\n310:       );\n311:       const json = await res.json();\n312:       return json.data;\n313:     },\n314:   });\n315: }\n316: ```\n317: \n318: ### createResource → React Query mapping\n319: \n320: | frappe-ui (Vue) | React Query equivalent |\n321: |---|---|\n322: | `createResource({ url, … })` | `useQuery({ queryFn: () => fetch(url), … })` |\n323: | `createListResource({ doctype, … })` | `useQuery({ queryFn: () => frappe.getList(doctype, …), … })` |\n324: | `resource.submit()` | `useMutation({ mutationFn: … })` |\n325: | `resource.data` | `query.data` |\n326: | `resource.loading` | `query.isLoading` |\n327: | `resource.error` | `query.error` |\n328: | `resource.reload()` | `queryClient.invalidateQueries([key])` |\n329: \n330: ---\n331: \n332: ## Where frappe-ui is already used in this codebase\n333: \n334: Currently: **nowhere** — the prototype uses shadcn/ui throughout.\n335: \n336: After migration, frappe-ui tokens and (in the Vue production shell) components would replace:\n337: \n338: | Prototype file | frappe-ui replacement |\n339: |---|---|\n340: | `src/components/ui/button.tsx` | `<Button>` or `FGButton` shim |\n341: | `src/components/ui/input.tsx` | `<TextInput>` or frappe-ui tokens |\n342: | `src/components/ui/dialog.tsx` | `<Dialog>` |\n343: | `src/components/ui/tabs.tsx` | `<Tabs>` |\n344: | `src/components/ui/badge.tsx` | Inline frappe-ui token classes |\n345: | `src/components/ui/select.tsx` | `<FormControl>` with Select |\n346: | `src/components/ui/textarea.tsx` | `<TextareaInput>` |\n347: | `src/components/ui/avatar.tsx` | `<Avatar>` |\n348: | `src/components/ui/scroll-area.tsx` | Native overflow with frappe-ui classes |\n349: | `src/components/ui/tooltip.tsx` | `<Tooltip>` |\n350: | `src/components/ui/dropdown-menu.tsx` | `<DropdownMenu>` |\n351: | `src/components/AppLayout.tsx` | Keep structure, apply frappe-ui tokens |\n352: | `src/components/PostCard.tsx` | Keep structure, apply frappe-ui tokens |\n353: | `src/mock-data/store.ts` | Replace with `createListResource` + `createResource` |\n354: \n355: ---\n356: \n357: ## Migration checklist\n358: \n359: ```\n360: [ ] Install frappe-ui: bun add frappe-ui\n361: [ ] Import frappe-ui.css before Tailwind in styles.css\n362: [ ] Add frappe-ui Tailwind preset to tailwind.config.ts\n363: [ ] Run: bun run dev — verify no visual regressions\n364: [ ] Replace --background with --surface-base in styles.css\n365: [ ] Replace --foreground with --ink-base\n366: [ ] Replace --muted-foreground with --ink-gray-5\n367: [ ] Replace --border with --outline-gray-2\n368: [ ] Replace --primary with --surface-gray-10\n369: [ ] Create FGButton shim using frappe-ui token classes\n370: [ ] Create FGTextInput shim using frappe-ui token classes\n371: [ ] Create FGTabs shim using frappe-ui token classes\n372: [ ] Update AppLayout.tsx to use frappe-ui sidebar token classes\n373: [ ] Update PostCard.tsx to use frappe-ui card token classes\n374: [ ] Update SentimentBadge.tsx to use frappe-ui badge tokens\n375: [ ] When moving to Vue production shell:\n376:     [ ] Install Vue 3, vue-router, frappe-ui\n377:     [ ] Replace React components with Vue SFCs\n378:     [ ] Replace TanStack Query with createResource / createListResource\n379:     [ ] Replace TanStack Router with vue-router\n380:     [ ] Wire real Frappe session cookie auth\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ---\n384: \n385: ## Frappe-ui data layer — `createResource` deep dive\n386: \n387: This is the most important part of the frappe-ui migration. Today the prototype uses a hand-rolled in-memory store. The production version uses `createResource` (Vue) or TanStack Query (React).\n388: \n389: ### Reading a list (Vue + frappe-ui)\n390: \n391: ```vue\n392: <script setup>\n393: import { createListResource } from \"frappe-ui\";\n394: \n395: const spaces = createListResource({\n396:   doctype: \"GP Project\",\n397:   fields: [\"name\", \"title\", \"icon\", \"description\", \"is_private\", \"discussions_count\"],\n398:   filters: [[\"is_private\", \"=\", 0]],\n399:   orderBy: \"title asc\",\n400:   pageLength: 50,\n401:   auto: true,          // fetch immediately on mount\n402:   transform(rows) {\n403:     // Rename Frappe `name` to `id` to match prototype shape\n404:     return rows.map(r => ({ ...r, id: r.name }));\n405:   },\n406: });\n407: </script>\n408: \n409: <template>\n410:   <div v-if=\"spaces.loading\">Loading…</div>\n411:   <div v-else-if=\"spaces.error\">{{ spaces.error.message }}</div>\n412:   <SpaceCard v-for=\"s in spaces.data\" :key=\"s.id\" :space=\"s\" />\n413: </template>\n414: ```\n415: \n416: ### Creating a document (Vue + frappe-ui)\n417: \n418: ```vue\n419: <script setup>\n420: import { createResource } from \"frappe-ui\";\n421: \n422: const createPost = createResource({\n423:   url: \"frappe.client.insert\",\n424:   makeParams({ title, content, project }) {\n425:     return {\n426:       doc: { doctype: \"GP Discussion\", title, content, project },\n427:     };\n428:   },\n429:   onSuccess(data) {\n430:     // Invalidate the list so it refreshes\n431:     spaces.fetch();\n432:     emit(\"close\");\n433:   },\n434: });\n435: </script>\n436: \n437: <template>\n438:   <Button :loading=\"createPost.loading\" @click=\"createPost.submit({ title, content, project })\">\n439:     Post\n440:   </Button>\n441: </template>\n442: ```\n443: \n444: ### Custom RPC endpoint (Vue + frappe-ui)\n445: \n446: ```vue\n447: <script setup>\n448: import { createResource } from \"frappe-ui\";\n449: \n450: const rsvp = createResource({\n451:   url: \"fg_companion.api.rsvp\",\n452:   makeParams({ event, status }) {\n453:     return { event, rsvp_status: status };\n454:   },\n455:   onSuccess() {\n456:     toast(\"RSVP saved!\");\n457:   },\n458: });\n459: </script>\n460: ```\n461: \n462: ### React (TanStack Query) equivalent during transition\n463: \n464: ```tsx\n465: // src/data/mutations.ts\n466: import { useMutation, useQueryClient } from \"@tanstack/react-query\";\n467: \n468: function getCSRF(): string {\n469:   return (document.cookie.match(/csrftoken=([^;]+)/) ?? [])[1] ?? \"\";\n470: }\n471: \n472: async function rpc<T>(method: string, body: unknown): Promise<T> {\n473:   const res = await fetch(`/api/method/${method}`, {\n474:     method: \"POST\",\n475:     headers: {\n476:       \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n477:       \"X-Frappe-CSRF-Token\": getCSRF(),\n478:     },\n479:     credentials: \"include\",\n480:     body: JSON.stringify(body),\n481:   });\n482:   if (!res.ok) throw new Error(await res.text());\n483:   const json = (await res.json()) as { message: T };\n484:   return json.message;\n485: }\n486: \n487: export function useRsvp() {\n488:   const qc = useQueryClient();\n489:   return useMutation({\n490:     mutationFn: ({ event, status }: { event: string; status: string }) =>\n491:       rpc(\"fg_companion.api.rsvp\", { event, rsvp_status: status }),\n492:     onSuccess: () => qc.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: [\"events\"] }),\n493:   });\n494: }\n495: ```\n496: \n497: ---\n498: \n499: ## Visual regression testing strategy\n500: \n501: When applying frappe-ui tokens, run the prototype side-by-side to catch regressions:\n502: \n503: 1. Start the current prototype: `bun run dev` → `http://localhost:3000`\n504: 2. Screenshot each page (using Playwright or manually)\n505: 3. Apply token changes\n506: 4. Re-screenshot and diff\n507: \n508: Key screens to verify:\n509: - Home feed (PostCard, SentimentBadge)\n510: - Space page (Space header, post list)\n511: - Post detail (comment thread, reactions, similar posts)\n512: - Events grid (RSVP button states)\n513: - Mentor match page (match cards, request form)\n514: - Settings panel (all tabs)\n515: - Course player (YouTube embed, lesson navigation)\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ## WCAG 2.2 AA compliance notes\n520: \n521: frappe-ui is built to WCAG 2.2 AA. Key requirements to verify after migration:\n522: \n523: | Requirement | frappe-ui coverage |\n524: |---|---|\n525: | Colour contrast ≥ 4.5:1 for normal text | ✅ `ink-gray-*` palette is calibrated |\n526: | Focus indicators visible | ✅ `focus-ring` utility class |\n527: | Interactive targets ≥ 24×24px | ✅ Minimum `h-7` (28px) on all controls |\n528: | Error messages programmatically associated | ✅ `<FormControl>` links label + error |\n529: | Keyboard navigation | ✅ Radix primitives handle this |\n530: | Screen reader labels | ⚠️ Verify custom icon buttons have `aria-label` |\n531: \n532: ---\n533: \n534: ## Estimated migration effort\n535: \n536: | Task | Effort |\n537: |---|---|\n538: | Install frappe-ui, apply CSS tokens | 0.5 day |\n539: | Create React shims (Button, Input, Tabs, Dialog) | 1 day |\n540: | Apply tokens to AppLayout, PostCard, SentimentBadge | 1 day |\n541: | Apply tokens to all routes (19 files) | 2 days |\n542: | Visual regression check + fixes | 1 day |\n543: | **Total (React token migration)** | **~1 week** |\n544: | Vue 3 component migration (production) | 2 weeks |\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ## References\n549: \n550: - [frappe-ui GitHub](https://github.com/frappe/frappe-ui)\n551: - [frappe-ui documentation](https://ui.frappe.io/docs/getting-started)\n552: - [frappe-ui component list](https://ui.frappe.io)\n553: - [frappe-ui Tailwind preset](https://github.com/frappe/frappe-ui/blob/main/src/utils/tailwind.config.js)\n554: - [Gameplan frontend (Vue + frappe-ui reference)](https://github.com/frappe/gameplan/tree/main/frontend)\n555: - [Frappe LMS frontend (Vue + frappe-ui reference)](https://github.com/frappe/lms/tree/main/frontend)\n556: - [Raven frontend (Vue + frappe-ui + React Native)](https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven)\n\n(End of file - total 556 lines)\n</content>",
