      "type": "action",
      "tool": "read",
      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\community-launchpad-proto\\\\docs\\\\05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md\"}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto\\docs\\05_CIRCLE_TO_FRAPPE_MAPPING.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # 05 — Circle.so → Frappe feature mapping\n2: \n3: Every meaningful Circle.so surface, and how it ports onto the Frappe stack\n4: (`frappe/frappe` + `frappe/gameplan` + `frappe/lms` + a thin custom\n5: `fg_companion` app). No invented Frappe features — every row below points at\n6: something that already ships in the named repo or is a documented Custom\n7: Field / DocType pattern.\n8: \n9: Symbols used in the \"How\" column:\n10: - **GP** = lives in `frappe/gameplan` (existing DocType, no fork)\n11: - **LMS** = lives in `frappe/lms` (existing DocType, no fork)\n12: - **CORE** = ships in `frappe/frappe`\n13: - **+CF** = same DocType, extended via Custom Field fixture in `fg_companion`\n14: - **NEW** = new DocType in `fg_companion`\n15: \n16: ## Community surface\n17: \n18: | Circle.so concept | FirstGens / Frappe equivalent | How |\n19: | --- | --- | --- |\n20: | Community | Frappe Site (one site per community) | CORE |\n21: | Space Group | `GP Team` | GP |\n22: | Space | `GP Project` | GP |\n23: | Post | `GP Discussion` | GP |\n24: | Comment | `GP Comment` | GP |\n25: | Reaction (emoji) | `GP Reaction` (istable child) | GP |\n26: | Pinned post | `GP Discussion.pinned_at` / `pinned_by` | GP |\n27: | Closed thread | `GP Discussion.closed_at` / `closed_by` | GP |\n28: | @mention | `frappe.utils.mentions` parser + Notification | CORE |\n29: | Direct Messages | Raven (`frappe/raven`) embedded panel | Ecosystem — see doc 06 |\n30: | Member directory | List view over `User` + `GP User Profile` | GP + CORE |\n31: | Member profile | `GP User Profile` | GP |\n32: | Profile cover image | `GP User Profile.cover_image` | GP |\n33: | Following a member | `GP Follow` | GP |\n34: | Bookmark a post | `GP Bookmark` | GP |\n35: | Notifications inbox | `Notification Log` | CORE |\n36: | Notification preferences | `Notification Settings` + `FG User Settings` | CORE +NEW |\n37: | Search across community | Frappe Global Search + Postgres `pg_trgm` index | CORE |\n38: | Roles & permissions | Role + Role Profile + DocPerm | CORE |\n39: | Audit log | `Activity Log` / `Version` | CORE |\n40: \n41: ## Events surface\n42: \n43: | Circle.so | FirstGens / Frappe | How |\n44: | --- | --- | --- |\n45: | Event | `FG Event` | NEW |\n46: | RSVP | `FG Event Attendee.rsvp_status` | NEW |\n47: | Recurring events | Custom Field `recurrence_rule` (RFC 5545) | +CF |\n48: | Hosted webinar room | BigBlueButton integration (`frappe-bbb` pattern) | NEW glue |\n49: | External link event | `FG Event.external_link` | NEW |\n50: | Calendar export (.ics) | `@frappe.whitelist()` endpoint returning text/calendar | NEW |\n51: | Reminders | Frappe Scheduled Job → `Email Queue` | CORE |\n52: \n53: ## Courses surface (THIS IS WHY WE PICKED FRAPPE)\n54: \n55: | Circle.so paid feature | FirstGens / Frappe | How |\n56: | --- | --- | --- |\n57: | Course | `LMS Course` | LMS |\n58: | Chapter | `LMS Chapter` | LMS |\n59: | Lesson (text/video) | `LMS Lesson` (Markdown + `{{ YouTubeVideo(\"...\") }}`) | LMS |\n60: | Lesson video (YouTube) | `youtube_video` shortcode rendered by LMS template | LMS |\n61: | Lesson video (upload) | `File` doctype + LMS video player | LMS + CORE |\n62: | Quiz | `LMS Quiz` + `LMS Question` | LMS |\n63: | Assignment | `LMS Assignment` + `LMS Assignment Submission` | LMS |\n64: | Enrollment | `LMS Enrollment` | LMS |\n65: | Progress | `LMS Course Progress` (per-lesson) | LMS |\n66: | Certificate on completion | `LMS Certificate` + PDF print format | LMS |\n67: | Cohort / Batch | `LMS Batch` + `LMS Batch Membership` | LMS |\n68: | Live class | `LMS Live Class` (BBB or external) | LMS |\n69: | Instructor profile | `Course Instructor` child table on LMS Course | LMS |\n70: | Paywall | `LMS Course.paid_course` + payment gateway | LMS |\n71: | Discussions inside a course | Frappe Comment thread on `LMS Course` | LMS + CORE |\n72: \n73: ## Profile / Settings surface\n74: \n75: | Circle.so | Frappe | How |\n76: | --- | --- | --- |\n77: | Public profile page | `GP User Profile` | GP |\n78: | Edit profile inline | Same DocType, `frappe.client.set_value` | GP |\n79: | Notification preferences | `Notification Settings` | CORE |\n80: | Privacy: hide from directory | `FG User Settings.show_in_member_directory` | NEW |\n81: | Privacy: DMs from anyone | `FG User Settings.allow_dm_from_anyone` | NEW |\n82: | Theme (light/dark/system) | `User.desk_theme` + frontend toggle | CORE |\n83: | Language | `User.language` | CORE |\n84: | Timezone | `User.time_zone` | CORE |\n85: | Sessions / sign-out | `Sessions` + `frappe.local.login_manager.logout()` | CORE |\n86: | 2FA | Built-in TOTP / Email OTP | CORE |\n87: \n88: ## Moderation / Safeguarding (FG-specific layer)\n89: \n90: | Need | How |\n91: | --- | --- |\n92: | Sentiment flag on new posts | `doc_events` on `GP Discussion.after_insert` → enqueue `analyse_sentiment` background job → writes `fg_sentiment_label` + `fg_sentiment_score` Custom Fields |\n93: | Moderator triage queue | List view on `GP Discussion` filtered by `fg_sentiment_label = 'Needs Attention'` |\n94: | Quiet check-in DM | Raven message template fired by the same job |\n95: | Audit who reviewed a flag | `fg_reviewed_by` + `fg_reviewed_at` Custom Fields |\n96: | Vector \"similar discussions\" | `pgvector` extension + `fg_embedding` Custom Field populated by background job |\n97: \n98: All four of the FG-specific Custom Fields live in\n99: `fg_companion/fg_companion/fixtures/custom_field.json` — they're applied via\n100: `bench migrate`, never by forking gameplan.\n101: \n102: ## What we deliberately don't port from Circle\n103: \n104: - Circle's proprietary \"Workflows\" engine → Frappe Workflow on the relevant\n105:   DocType plus a Server Script if conditional steps are needed.\n106: - Circle's hosted video transcoding → out of scope; YouTube embed covers 95%\n107:   of community use, large uploads go to S3 with the LMS video field.\n108: - Circle's \"AI Inbox\" reply suggestions → opt-in; can be added later as a\n109:   Frappe Server Script calling Ollama or the configured LLM provider.\n\n(End of file - total 109 lines)\n</content>",
