      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\community-launchpad-proto\\\\docs\\\\08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md\"}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto\\docs\\08_FRAPPE_GAP_ANALYSIS.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # 08 — Frappe Ecosystem Gap Analysis (Circle.so → Frappe)\n2: \n3: Audit of every Frappe-ecosystem app/module that could replace a Circle.so feature for the FirstGens Community platform. Rating: ⭐ production / 🟡 partial-or-early / 🔴 abandoned-or-missing.\n4: \n5: ## Summary matrix\n6: \n7: | # | Circle feature | Best Frappe option | Repo / module | Status | Gap |\n8: |---|---|---|---|---|---|\n9: | 1 | Direct messages, channels, threads | **Raven** | github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven | ⭐ | None — has React Native mobile |\n10: | 2 | Notifications (in-app + email) | Frappe Framework core | github.com/frappe/frappe | ⭐ | Push needs FCM glue |\n11: | 3 | Live events / video | **frappe/meet** (WebRTC) + LMS Zoom/BBB | github.com/frappe/meet, github.com/frappe/lms | 🟡 | No broadcast/webinar; **Teams integration is custom** (see ADR-003) |\n12: | 4 | Member directory (public, filterable) | — (LMS profile is course-centric) | — | 🔴 | Build on Framework |\n13: | 5 | Paywalls / membership tiers | frappe/payments + ERPNext Subscription | github.com/frappe/payments | 🟡 | No Space-gating UX |\n14: | 6 | Email digests | frappe/newsletter | github.com/frappe/newsletter | 🟡 | Engine only, no \"this-week-in\" generator |\n15: | 7 | Helpdesk / safeguarding tickets | **frappe/helpdesk** | github.com/frappe/helpdesk | ⭐ | None |\n16: | 8 | Community moderation (word filters, AI flag, queues, appeals) | — | — | 🔴 | Build on Framework |\n17: | 9 | Wiki / knowledge base | **frappe/wiki** | github.com/frappe/wiki | ⭐ | None |\n18: | 10 | Polls / surveys | frappe/poll (abandoned 2016); LMS quizzes for course context | — | 🔴 | Build on Framework |\n19: | 11 | Gamification / badges | **frappe/eps** (Energy Points) | github.com/frappe/eps | ⭐ | Points & leaderboards yes; visual badge UI no |\n20: | 12 | Global search | Framework SQLite FTS5 (July 2025) | github.com/frappe/frappe | ⭐ | Cross-content wiring needed |\n21: | 13 | Analytics / BI | **frappe/insights** | github.com/frappe/insights | ⭐ | No prebuilt community dashboards |\n22: | 14 | AI / automation | Server Scripts + Workflows + **otto** (upcoming) + Raven AI bot | github.com/frappe/frappe, surajshetty3416/otto | ⭐ / 🟡 | No AI moderation app |\n23: | 15 | Mobile | Raven mobile (chat) + Capacitor PWA pattern (hrms reference) | The-Commit-Company/Raven, frappe/hrms | 🟡 | No full community app |\n24: | 16 | SSO / OAuth2 / SAML | Framework core | github.com/frappe/frappe | ⭐ | None |\n25: | 17 | Space concept | — (closest: Gameplan `GP Project`) | github.com/frappe/gameplan | 🔴 | Custom DocType `fg_space` extending GP Project |\n26: \n27: ## Build-from-scratch bucket (Frappe Framework custom app `fg_companion`)\n28: \n29: 1. **`fg_space`** — Circle's core \"Space\" abstraction. Extends `GP Project` with: `visibility` (public/private/secret), `paywall_plan` (link to subscription plan), `space_type` (feed / wiki / course / events), `moderator_role`.\n30: 2. **`fg_member_directory`** — public profile view, server-side filtering by skills, interests, year-group, region; opt-in/opt-out flag on `User`.\n31: 3. **`fg_moderation_rule`** + **`fg_moderation_queue`** + **`fg_appeal`** — word/regex filters, AI confidence threshold, trusted-reviewer role, appeal workflow.\n32: 4. **`fg_poll`** + **`fg_poll_vote`** — single/multi/anonymous polls embedded in posts, chart in feed card.\n33: 5. **`fg_paywall_grant`** — joins `ERPNext Subscription` → `fg_space` membership; nightly job revokes on lapse.\n34: 6. **`fg_digest_job`** — server script that queries last-7-day activity per user's joined spaces and renders into a Newsletter template.\n35: 7. **`fg_badge`** + **`fg_badge_award`** — visual badge graphics on top of EPS point thresholds.\n36: \n37: ## Already-built bucket (just install + theme)\n38: \n39: ```bash\n40: bench get-app raven       https://github.com/The-Commit-Company/Raven\n41: bench get-app wiki        https://github.com/frappe/wiki\n42: bench get-app helpdesk    https://github.com/frappe/helpdesk\n43: bench get-app insights    https://github.com/frappe/insights\n44: bench get-app eps         https://github.com/frappe/eps\n45: bench get-app newsletter  https://github.com/frappe/newsletter\n46: bench get-app lms         https://github.com/frappe/lms\n47: bench get-app meet        https://github.com/frappe/meet   # optional, early\n48: bench --site <site> install-app raven wiki helpdesk insights eps newsletter lms\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ## Microsoft Teams (live events) — developer-mode plan\n52: \n53: Frappe has no Teams app. ADR-003 covers full design; summary:\n54: \n55: - **Server Script** posts to Microsoft Graph `/me/onlineMeetings` using delegated OAuth2 (Azure AD app reg).\n56: - New `fg_live_event` DocType stores `provider` (teams | meet | zoom | bbb), `join_url`, `recording_url`.\n57: - **Settings page** in the prototype already has a \"Microsoft Teams\" tab — it surfaces the steps the admin must perform in their Azure tenant (create App Registration, grant `OnlineMeetings.ReadWrite`, paste client id/secret/tenant id). Nothing in this prototype calls Teams; the settings tab documents the production wire-up.\n58: - For the FG production port, prefer **frappe/meet** for internal calls and **Teams** for cross-org events with external attendees (schools, councils).\n59: \n60: See ADR-003 for Gherkin acceptance and decision rationale.\n\n(End of file - total 60 lines)\n</content>",
