      "code": "{\"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\community-launchpad-proto\\\\docs\\\\03_PORTING_GUIDE.md\"}",
      "output": "<path>C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\community-launchpad-proto\\docs\\03_PORTING_GUIDE.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Porting Guide: Prototype → Production Frappe Stack\n2: \n3: The prototype is intentionally a thin React skin over a typed mock store.\n4: This document is the concrete recipe for moving it onto the real backend.\n5: \n6: ## Target architecture\n7: \n8: ```\n9: Frappe bench\n10: ├── apps/frappe          (the framework itself)\n11: ├── apps/lms             (frappe/lms — courses, lessons, quizzes)\n12: ├── apps/gameplan        (frappe/gameplan — teams, spaces, discussions, comments, reactions)\n13: └── apps/fg_companion    (NEW custom app — events, mentor matching, AI hooks, AI settings)\n14: ```\n15: \n16: The React frontend stays. It talks to Frappe over the standard\n17: `/api/method/...` and `/api/resource/...` HTTP endpoints (or via a thin\n18: client wrapper).\n19: \n20: ## Step 0 — provisioning\n21: \n22: ```bash\n23: bench init firstgens-bench --frappe-branch version-15\n24: cd firstgens-bench\n25: bench new-site firstgens.local\n26: \n27: bench get-app https://github.com/frappe/lms\n28: bench get-app https://github.com/frappe/gameplan\n29: bench --site firstgens.local install-app lms gameplan\n30: \n31: # Create the new custom app\n32: bench new-app fg_companion\n33: bench --site firstgens.local install-app fg_companion\n34: ```\n35: \n36: ## Step 1 — keep the gameplan DocTypes as-is\n37: \n38: **Do not fork gameplan.** Use `GP Team`, `GP Project`, `GP Discussion`,\n39: `GP Comment`, `GP Reaction`, `GP User Profile` exactly as shipped. The\n40: prototype's TypeScript shapes already match these field names — see\n41: [`01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md`](./01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md).\n42: \n43: If you need extra fields (e.g. for the sentiment flag), add them as\n44: **Custom Fields** on the gameplan DocType from inside `fg_companion`'s\n45: fixtures. This survives `bench update` and avoids merge conflicts.\n46: \n47: ## Step 2 — define the new DocTypes inside `fg_companion`\n48: \n49: Create these DocTypes in the `fg_companion` app with the exact field names\n50: listed in [`01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md`](./01_SCHEMA_MAPPING_TO_FRAPPE.md):\n51: \n52: - `FG Event`\n53: - `FG Event Attendee`\n54: - `FG Mentor Match`\n55: - `FG AI Settings` (Single)\n56: \n57: Then export them as fixtures (`bench --site … export-fixtures --app\n58: fg_companion`) so they version-control cleanly.\n59: \n60: ## Step 3 — wire the AI features as `doc_events`, not forks\n61: \n62: In `apps/fg_companion/fg_companion/hooks.py`:\n63: \n64: ```python\n65: doc_events = {\n66:     \"GP Discussion\": {\n67:         \"after_insert\": \"fg_companion.ai.sentiment.enqueue_score\",\n68:         \"on_update\":   \"fg_companion.ai.sentiment.enqueue_score\",\n69:     },\n70:     \"GP Comment\": {\n71:         \"after_insert\": \"fg_companion.ai.sentiment.enqueue_score\",\n72:         \"on_update\":   \"fg_companion.ai.sentiment.enqueue_score\",\n73:     },\n74: }\n75: ```\n76: \n77: Then in `fg_companion/ai/sentiment.py`:\n78: \n79: 1. Read `FG AI Settings`. If `enable_sentiment == 0`, return immediately.\n80: 2. Enqueue a Frappe background job (`frappe.enqueue`) that runs an ONNX\n81:    sentiment model against the doc's `content`.\n82: 3. Write the result to **Custom Fields** added to `GP Discussion` /\n83:    `GP Comment` (e.g. `fg_sentiment_label`, `fg_sentiment_score`) — never\n84:    modify gameplan's own fields.\n85: \n86: Mirror this pattern for vector search in `fg_companion/ai/vectors.py`:\n87: \n88: 1. Embed `title + content` with EmbeddingGemma (or another small open\n89:    embedding model).\n90: 2. Upsert into pgvector (Postgres on the Frappe site) keyed by\n91:    `GP Discussion.name`.\n92: 3. Expose `fg_companion.api.similar_discussions(name)` that runs an ANN\n93:    query filtered by Space + the calling user's gameplan permissions.\n94: \n95: Both features must respect `FG AI Settings` as a global kill-switch.\n96: \n97: ## Step 4 — swap the React data layer\n98: \n99: Right now, every page imports selectors and mutators from\n100: `src/mock-data/store.ts`. Replace that one file (or shadow it with a\n101: sibling) with a Frappe HTTP client:\n102: \n103: ```ts\n104: // src/mock-data/store.ts  →  src/data/store.ts\n105: export async function getDiscussions(projectId?: string) {\n106:   const params = projectId\n107:     ? `?filters=${encodeURIComponent(JSON.stringify([[\"project\",\"=\",projectId]]))}`\n108:     : \"\";\n109:   const res = await fetch(`/api/resource/GP Discussion${params}`);\n110:   // map to the same GPDiscussion shape the components already expect\n111: }\n112: ```\n113: \n114: Because **the TypeScript types stay the same**, no component changes.\n115: \n116: For the AI bits:\n117: - Sentiment label/score is now a field on the doc → read directly.\n118: - Similar posts becomes `fetch(\"/api/method/fg_companion.api.similar_discussions?name=...\")`.\n119: \n120: ## Step 5 — auth + permissions\n121: \n122: - Use Frappe's session cookie auth (default for the bench).\n123: - Set role-based permissions on `FG Event`, `FG Event Attendee`,\n124:   `FG Mentor Match`, and `FG AI Settings`. Match gameplan's existing\n125:   \"Space Member\" / \"Space Admin\" conventions.\n126: - The mocked sentiment \"Flagged for check-in\" badge should be visible\n127:   **only to Space Admins** in production. In the prototype it's visible to\n128:   everyone because there are no real roles.\n129: \n130: ## Step 6 — what to throw away from the prototype\n131: \n132: - `src/mock-data/seed.ts` — replaced by real data.\n133: - `src/mock-data/store.ts` — replaced by a Frappe client.\n134: - `mockSentiment()` and `findSimilarPosts()` — replaced by the Frappe\n135:   doc_events pipeline above.\n136: \n137: What stays:\n138: - All of `src/routes/*` (pages + URL structure).\n139: - All of `src/components/*` (visual design + interactions).\n140: - `src/mock-data/types.ts` (rename to `src/data/types.ts`) — these are the\n141:   canonical TS shapes and they already match Frappe.\n142: - This `/docs` folder.\n\n(End of file - total 142 lines)\n</content>",
