    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me analyze what's working and what needs fixing based on the Gherkin scenarios and the current state of the code.\n\nLooking at the Gherkin scenarios and the current codebase:\n\n1. **DMs (Raven)** - Gherkin says: \"When she clicks 'Message Joel' from the match card, Then a Raven DM channel opens with Joel\"\n   - Current: MentorsView has match cards but no \"Message\" button on the match cards\n   - Fix: Add \"Message\" button to mentor match cards\n   \n2. **Events (Teams)** - Gherkin says: Admin creates Teams event with \"Join on Teams\" button\n   - Current: EventsView shows events with RSVP but no Teams integration UI\n   - This is backend-only, prototype can't fully implement\n\n3. **Member Directory** - Gherkin says: Filterable by skills, region, with \"Message\" and \"Request mentor match\" buttons\n   - Current: MembersView shows a grid but no filters, no \"Message\" or \"Request mentor match\" buttons\n   - Fix: Add filters and action buttons\n\n4. **Paywall** - Gherkin says: Lock screen with plan name, price, \"Subscribe\" CTA\n   - Current: No paywall implementation\n   - This is a future feature, not in prototype scope\n\n5. **Moderation** - Gherkin says: Post held for review with banner\n   - Current: SentimentBadge shows \"Flagged for check-in\" but no moderation queue UI\n   - This is mostly backend, prototype shows the badge\n\n6. **Polls** - Gherkin says: Vote on poll in feed, show percentages\n   - Current: No poll implementation\n   - Need to add poll types and UI\n\n7. **Gamification** - Gherkin says: First post awards badge, shows in profile\n   - Current: No gamification/badges in prototype\n   - Need to add badge system\n\n8. **Mobile** - Gherkin says: Push notifications\n   - This is native app territory, not prototype scope\n\n9. **AI bot** - Gherkin says: Bot replies in channel\n   - Current: No AI bot\n   - This is future feature\n\n10. **Community digest** - Gherkin says: Weekly email\n    - This is backend, not prototype scope\n\n11. **Cross-space activity feed** - Gherkin says: Posts from joined spaces interleaved by rank\n    - Current: HomeView shows all posts sorted by recency\n    - This is already working as intended\n\nNow I need to prioritize what I can actually implement in the prototype: add \"Message\" button to mentor match cards, add filters and action buttons to MembersView, add poll types and UI, and implement the badge system for gamification.\n\nLooking at the broader scope, I should also fix the AppLayout routing issue since views need proper wrappers, ensure SpaceView displays correctly, make sure NewPostModal opens from the sidebar, and add toast notifications for user feedback. The main gaps are adding mentor message buttons to match cards, creating a moderation queue view, implementing poll voting with display, adding badges to profiles, and creating a \"Message\" button on member cards.\n\nThe user wants me to ensure all the Frappe libraries are properly integrated for this project—Frappe Discuss, LMS, and related services. Since we're in prototype mode, I need to focus on making sure the mock data layer is complete and functional, then work through the view fixes systematically to ensure each one renders and operates correctly.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the core user flows that need to work: creating and viewing posts with reactions and comments, messaging between users, RSVPing to events, requesting mentor matches, enrolling in courses and tracking progress, browsing the member directory with filters, managing notifications, and adjusting settings. The main issues I'm seeing are that several views like SpaceView aren't properly wrapped in AppLayout, the MembersView lacks the action buttons users need, and the mentor cards are missing messaging functionality. I'll need to add toast notifications for better UX and fill in the missing pieces like the \"Message\" button on mentor cards, proper space context in posts, and course management features. Looking at what the user actually needs - they want all the user journeys working with Frappe libraries integrated. The views that need fixing are HomeView, SpaceView, and PostDetailView to use AppLayout properly, plus MentorsView needs message buttons and MembersView needs action buttons. I should also add toast notifications for better feedback and create a settings page to complete the experience.",
