      "text": "The user is asking why there are no Frappe apps running. This is a question about the architecture decisions - not a task to execute. Let me answer directly.\n\nThe reason is that this is a prototype/MVP stage. Frappe apps require a full bench setup (Python, MariaDB/PostgreSQL, Redis, etc.) which is heavy infrastructure. The prototype is designed to:\n\n1. Run standalone without any backend infrastructure\n2. Be developed and tested quickly in a browser\n3. Demonstrate the UX and business logic before committing to the full stack\n4. Allow rapid iteration on the UI without server restarts\n\nWhen ready for production, the plan is to port to actual Frappe apps - the types are already 1:1 mapped to make that transition smooth.",
