      "text": "Sudo requires a password — I can't install system packages (MariaDB, Redis, etc.) without it.\n\n**Two options:**\n\n1. **You set NOPASSWD for your WSL user** (recommended — one-time setup):\n   Open a WSL terminal and run:\n   ```bash\n   sudo visudo\n   ```\n   Add this line at the end (replace `andieko` with your actual username):\n   ```\n   andieko ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL\n   ```\n   Save and exit. Then tell me to continue.\n\n2. **You run the install steps manually** — I give you the commands to paste into WSL.\n\nWhich do you prefer? Or what's your WSL username so I can give you the exact commands?",
