      "text": "I can't open an interactive terminal from here — `sudo visudo` is an interactive text editor that requires you to type manually.\n\n**Open it yourself — takes 10 seconds:**\n\n1. Press `Win` key\n2. Type `ubuntu` or `wsl`\n3. Click the Ubuntu app\n4. Paste this and press Enter:\n   ```bash\n   echo 'andieko ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL' | sudo tee -a /etc/sudoers.d/nopasswd\n   ```\n5. Type your password when prompted\n6. Done — tell me \"done\"\n\nThat's faster than `visudo` and does the same thing.",
