    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The issue is that MariaDB root password is empty, but the site_config has a randomly generated db_password. The `bench new-site` creates a user with that random password, but then can't connect because the MariaDB root user setup is wrong. Let me check what's happening.\n\nThe problem might be that the `--mariadb-root-password ''` flag doesn't work as expected with bench 5.x, or MariaDB has been configured with a different root auth method (unix_socket vs password).\n\nLet me check the MariaDB auth method.",
      "timestamp": 1781954781359
