    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "I see the issue. The Procfile has redis using custom config files (`config/redis_cache.conf` and `config/redis_queue.conf`) on different ports (13000 and 11000), not the system Redis. I need to either:\n1. Start Redis with those custom configs, or\n2. Start bench (which starts everything via honcho)\n\nLet me start bench in the background, wait for it, then run migrate. Actually, bench migrate should work if I start bench first. But the problem is `bench start` is an interactive process that blocks. Let me run it in background, wait a bit, then try migrate.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully, the right approach is: run `bench start` in background, wait for services to come up, then use `bench --site firstgens.localhost migrate`. But since `bench start` runs all the services, the migrate needs to happen after they're up.\n\nWait, I think the better approach is to just start the services that bench needs to be happy (redis on those ports), then run migrate.",
