      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The user wants me to continue with the next steps. Looking at the progress, I need to:\n\n1. Fix the seed script - it's failing because `bench execute` expects a function path, not a file. I need to use `bench --site firstgens.localhost execute /tmp/seed_firstgens.py` with the right syntax.\n\nActually, let me check - the correct way to run a script with `bench execute` is:\n- `bench execute frappe.utils.bench_helper.execute` or\n- `bench --site firstgens.localhost execute /path/to/script.py` but this doesn't work as shown\n\nThe proper way is to put the file in the apps directory and use `bench --site firstgens.localhost execute fg_companion.seed_firstgens` but the module needs to be importable.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach - I'll write the seed script directly to a Python file in the WSL filesystem and use Python directly rather than `bench execute`:\n\n\nI can bypass the bench command entirely and use the Frappe Python environment directly to run my seeding script.",
