else feel like they don't belong at uni? I got good grades but constantly feel like I'm going to be found out.\\\"},\\n    {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Best resources for essay writing?\\\", \\\"project\\\": \\\"Study Tips & Resources\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"sam@firstgens.test\\\",\\n     \\\"content\\\": \\\"I'm in my first year and the jump from A-levels to uni essays is massive. Does anyone have good resources?\\\"},\\n    {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Networking events - how to actually do them?\\\", \\\"project\\\": \\\"Career Guidance\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"priya@firstgens.test\\\",\\n     \\\"content\\\": \\\"I went to a careers fair last week and had no idea what to say to the employers. How do you network?\\\"},\\n    {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Managing finances as a first-gen student\\\", \\\"project\\\": \\\"Navigating University\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"rosa@firstgens.test\\\",\\n     \\\"content\\\": \\\"First-gen students often don't have the financial safety net that others do. Happy to share what I've found.\\\"},\\n    {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Workshop recap: Building Your Support Network\\\", \\\"project\\\": \\\"Upcoming Events\\\", \\\"author\\\": \\\"jordan@firstgens.test\\\",\\n     \\\"content\\\": \\\"Great turnout at yesterday's workshop! Key takeaways: build relationships with your personal tutor.\\\"},\\n]\\n\\n# First check the GP Discussion doctype fields\\nfields = frappe.db.sql(\\\"DESCRIBE `tabGP Discussion`\\\", as_dict=True)\\nprint(f\\\"  GP Discussion columns: {[f.field for f in fields]}\\\")\\n\\nfor d in discussions:\\n    existing = frappe.db.get_value(\\\"GP Discussion\\\", {\\\"title\\\": d[\\\"title\\\"]}, \\\"name\\\")\\n    if not existing:\\n        try:\\n            disc = frappe.new_doc(\\\"GP Discussion\\\")\\n            disc.title = d[\\\"title\\\"]\\n            disc.content = d[\\\"content\\\"]\\n            disc.author_id = d[\\\"author\\\"]\\n            disc.project = d[\\\"project\\\"]\\n            disc.flags.ignore_permissions = True\\n            disc.insert()\\n            frappe.db.commit()\\n            print(f\\\"  Created discussion: {d['title'][:50]}...\\\")\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"  Discussion error '{d['title'][:30]}': {e}\\\")\\n\\n# ============================================\\n# LMS COURSES\\n# ============================================\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n=== Creating LMS Courses ===\\\")\\n\\n# Check LMS Course columns\\nfields = frappe.db.sql(\\\"DESCRIBE `tabLMS Course`\\\", as_dict=True)\\nprint(f\\\"  LMS Course columns: {[f.field for f in fields]}\\\")\\n\\n# Check LMS Course Category\\ncat_fields = frappe.db.sql(\\\"DESCRIBE `tabLMS Course Category`\\\", as_dict=True)\\nprint(f\\\"  LMS Course Category columns: {[f.field for f in cat_fields]}\\\")\\n\\ncourses = [\\n    {\\\"course_title\\\": \\\"Navigating University: A First-Gen Guide\\\", \\\"short_introduction\\\": \\\"Everything you need to know about surviving and thriving at university as a first-generation student.\\\", \\\"instructor\\\": \\\"alaya@firstgens.test\\\", \\\"published\\\": 1, \\\"enable_certification\\\": 1},\\n    {\\\"course_title\\\": \\\"Academic Writing for First-Gen Students\\\", \\\"short_introduction\\\": \\\"Master academic essay writing with techniques specifically designed for students new to university-level work.\\\", \\\"instructor\\\": \\\"jordan@firstgens.test\\\", \\\"published\\\": 1, \\\"enable_certification\\\": 1},\\n    {\\\"course_title\\\": \\\"Career Planning from Day One\\\", \\\"short_introduction\\\": \\\"Start thinking about your career from your first week at university.\\\", \\\"instructor\\\": \\\"priya@firstgens.test\\\", \\\"published\\\": 1, \\\"enable_certification\\\": 0},\\n]\\n\\nfor c in courses:\\n    existing = frappe.db.get_value(\\\"LMS Course\\\", {\\\"course_title\\\": c[\\\"course_title\\\"]}, \\\"name\\\")\\n    if not existing:\\n        try:\\n            course = frappe.new_doc(\\\"LMS Course\\\")\\n            course.update(c)\\n            course.flags.ignore_permissions = True\\n            course.insert()\\n            frappe.db.commit()\\n            print(f\\\"  Created course: {c['course_title']}\\\")\\n        except Exception as e:\\n            print(f\\\"  Course error '{c['course_title'][:30]}': {e}\\\")\\n\\n# ============================================\\n# HD TICKETS\\n# ============================================\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n=== Creating HD Tickets ===\\\")\\n\\n# Check HD Ticket columns\\nfields = frappe.db.sql(\\\"DESCRIBE `tabHD Ticket`\\\", as_dict=True)\\nprint(f\\\"  HD Ticket columns: {[f.field for f in fields]}\\\")\\n\\n# Check priorities\\nprio_fields = frappe.db.sql(\\\"DESCRIBE `tabHD Ticket Priority`\\\", as_dict=True)\\nprint(f\\\"  HD Ticket Priority columns: {[f.field for f in prio_fields]}\\\")\\n\\ntickets = [\\n    {\\\"subject\\\": \\\"Cannot access course materials on mobile\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Hi, I'm trying to access the Navigating University course on my phone but the videos won't load.\\\", \\\"status\\\": \\\"Open\\\", \\\"priority\\\": \\\"Medium\\\", \\\"ticket_type\\\": \\\"Bug\\\"},\\n    {\\\"subject\\\": \\\"Request for additional mentoring sessions\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"I'd really like to request more mentoring sessions. The weekly sessions are great but I have a lot of questions.\\\", \\\"status\\\": \\\"Open\\\", \\\"priority\\\": \\\"Low\\\", \\\"ticket_type\\\": \\\"Feature\\\"},\\n    {\\\"subject\\\": \\\"How do I update my profile photo?\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"I can't find where to change my profile picture. The settings page doesn't seem to have the option.\\\", \\\"status\\\": \\\"Replied\\\", \\\"priority\\\": \\\"Low\\\", \\\"ticket_type\\\": \\\"Feature\\\"},\\n]\\n\\nfor t in tickets:\\n    existing = frappe.db.get_value(\\\"HD Ticket\\\", {\\\"subject\\\": t[\\\"subject\\\"]}, \\\"name\\\")\\n    if not existing:\\n        try:\\n            ticket = frappe.new_doc(\\\"HD Ticket\\\")\\n   