      "text": "I see the login attempt returned **401 Unauthorized** - meaning the credentials didn't work. Let me check the user state and fix the issue:\n\n## Issue with FirstGens Users\n\nThe problem is likely in how I created the users during seeding. Let me check and fix the user accounts:\n\n**Expected users for FirstGens:**\n- alaya@firstgens.test (Founder)\n- jordan@firstgens.test, priya@firstgens.test, maya@firstgens.test (Mentors)\n- sam@firstgens.test, rosa@firstgens.test, alex@firstgens.test, fatima@firstgens.test (Students)\n\n**Login attempt:** `alaya@firstgens.test` with `firstgens123` → **401 Unauthorized**\n\n## Solutions:\n\n### 1. Reset All User Passwords\nThe easiest fix is to reset all FirstGens user passwords to `firstgens123`:\n\n```bash\n# Reset passwords for all FirstGens users\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\necho \"firstgens123\" | bench --site firstgens.localhost execute frappe.core.doctype.user.user.reset_password_for_user --args '[\"alaya@firstgens.test\"]'\necho \"firstgens123\" | bench --site firstgens.localhost execute frappe.core.doctype.user.user.reset_password_for_user --args '[\"jordan@firstgens.test\"]'\n# ... and repeat for all other users\n```\n\n### 2. Recreate Users from Scratch\nBetter approach is to delete existing FirstGens users and recreate them with proper Frappe user system:\n\n```bash\n# Delete all existing FirstGens users\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\nbench --site firstgens.localhost execute /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/sites/recreate_firstgens_users.py\n```\n\nWould you like me to create a script to fix the user accounts and ensure they can login properly?",
