      "text": "I understand you want the FirstGens platform to work seamlessly with Frappe framework and have coherent navigation that showcases your seeded data. However, this is a **complex architectural challenge** that requires more than simple fixes.\n\n## What Needs to Be Fixed\n\n### 🔧 **Navigation Integration Issues**\n- Frappe framework overlays your Vue.js FirstGens prototype\n- Default Frappe website menus interfere with custom navigation\n- User login redirects to Frappe website instead of your Vue.js app\n\n### 🏗️ **Data Integration Problems**\n- Seeded data exists but isn't properly connected to UI components\n- Discussion forums, LMS courses, tickets need custom Frappe hooks\n- Role-based access control needs to be implemented\n\n## Required Solution Architecture\n\n### **Phase 1: Custom Frappe App Creation**\nCreate a dedicated Frappe app (`fg_firstgens_app`) that:\n- Extends Frappe's website framework\n- Integrates your Vue.js components\n- Overrides default navigation\n- Provides custom user views\n\n### **Phase 2: Custom Website Routes**\n```python\n# In hooks.py\nwebsite_route_rules = [\n    {\"from_route\": \"/community\", \"to_route\": \"firstgens\"},\n    {\"from_route\": \"/community/<path:app_path>\", \"to_route\": \"firstgens\"},\n]\n```\n\n### **Phase 3: Custom User Views**\n- Override `get_website_user_communities()`\n- Create custom website templates\n- Implement role-based website dashboards\n\n### **Phase 4: Data Integration**\n- Create Frappe DocTypes for all seeded entities\n- Add website list views for discussions, courses, tickets\n- Implement proper filtering and search\n\n## Current Workaround (Short-term Solution)\n\n**For immediate functionality:**\n1. Use Frappe's website modules to display seeded data\n2. Create custom website templates for FirstGens\n3. Map seeded data to Frappe's existing data structures\n\n## What I Can Help You With Now\n\n### ✅ **Simple Fixes:**\n- Fix navigation menu display\n- Adjust user authentication flow\n- Add basic data display components\n\n### ⚠️ **Complex Tasks (Would require more time):**\n- Deep Frappe framework customization\n- Vue.js component integration\n- Advanced role-based access control\n- Custom website themes and branding\n\n## Recommended Next Steps\n\n### **Immediate (Can be done now):**\n1. Create a custom Frappe app with proper hooks\n2. Add website routes for FirstGens sections\n3. Create custom website templates\n4. Map seeded data to website views\n\n### **Medium-term (1-2 days):**\n1. Implement custom navigation menus\n2. Add role-based website access\n3. Create custom user dashboards\n\n### **Long-term (1 week):**\n1. Full Vue.js integration with Frappe\n2. Advanced community features\n3. Custom admin panels\n\n## Complexity Assessment\n\nThis is a **non-trivial integration** because:\n- Frappe and Vue.js have different architectural patterns\n- Seeding data vs. displaying it requires custom solutions\n- Navigation needs to bridge two different frameworks\n- User experience needs to be consistent across both systems\n\n**Would you like me to start with a custom Frappe app that integrates your FirstGens prototype?** This would be the foundation for fixing the navigation and data display issues.",
