      "type": "answer",
      "text": "## 🚨 **Root Cause - Python Module Import Error**\n\nThe error `No module named 'fg_firstgens_app'` indicates that Frappe cannot import your custom app. This is a classic Frappe app structure issue.\n\n## 🔍 **What's Happening**\n\nYour app exists at:\n```\n/home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_firstgens_app/\n```\n\nBut Frappe expects Python modules to be importable. The issue is that **Python cannot import modules from the apps directory** because it's not in the Python module search path.\n\n## 🛠️ **Solution - Create the Proper Python Module Structure**\n\nYou need to create the app as a proper Python package with `__init__.py` files at the right levels:\n\n```\nhome/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/\n├── env/                    # Virtual environment\n├── apps/\n│   ├── frappe/            # Frappe framework\n│   ├── gameplan/          # Other installed apps\n│   ├── lms/               # Other installed apps\n│   ├── helpdesk/          # Other installed apps\n│   ├── payments/          # Other installed apps\n│   └── fg_firstgens_app/  # ← Your custom app\n│       ├── __init__.py   ← Python package marker\n│       └── fg_firstgens_app/  ← Sub-package for hooks, etc.\n│           ├── __init__.py\n│           ├── patches/\n│           └── templates/\n```\n\n## ✅ **Quick Fix - Install Using Bench Command**\n\n**The easiest solution is to use the proper `bench new-app` command:**\n\n```bash\n# Stop the server first\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\nbench stop\n\n# Remove the incorrectly created app\nrm -rf /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench/apps/fg_firstgens_app\n\n# Create the app properly using bench\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\nbench new-app fg_firstgens_app --no-git\n\n# When prompted, use these values:\n# App Title: Fg Firstgens App\n# App Description: Community platform for first-generation students\n# Publisher: FirstGens\n# Email: admin@firstgens.test\n# License: mit\n# Frappe Version: version-15\n# Install now: y\n```\n\n## 📋 **After Installation**\n\nOnce properly installed, you can verify:\n\n```bash\ncd /home/andiekobbie/frappe-bench\nbench --site firstgens.localhost install-app fg_firstgens_app\n```\n\n## 🎯 **Key Points**\n\n1. **Frappe has specific app structure requirements**\n2. **The `bench new-app` command ensures proper setup**\n3. **Manual directory creation often fails to meet Python import requirements**\n4. **Using the official bench command guarantees compatibility**\n\n---\n\n**Use `bench new-app` for a reliable, properly structured Frappe custom app!** 🎉",
